fascinated with ancient Egypt.

00:07:45.540 --> 00:07:48.540 align:middle line:84%
Ancient Egypt was
antiquity itself

00:07:48.540 --> 00:07:50.170 align:middle line:90%
to the Hellenic civilizations.

00:07:50.170 --> 00:07:52.710 align:middle line:84%
And this has continued up
through the modern age,

00:07:52.710 --> 00:07:55.230 align:middle line:84%
particularly because
Egypt's language

00:07:55.230 --> 00:07:56.880 align:middle line:90%
is a symbolic language.

00:07:56.880 --> 00:08:00.610 align:middle line:10%
And even after it was
decoded, so to speak,

00:08:00.610 --> 00:08:04.110 align:middle line:10%
by the Rosetta Stone, it's still
retained many of its secrets

00:08:04.110 --> 00:08:08.280 align:middle line:10%
because Egypt's traditions were
oral traditions and traditions

00:08:08.280 --> 00:08:10.626 align:middle line:10%
encrypted within image
and architecture.

00:08:10.626 --> 00:08:17.430 align:middle line:90%


00:08:17.430 --> 00:08:18.230 align:middle line:90%
[END PLAYBACK]

00:08:18.230 --> 00:08:20.772 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Ah, you had to get a
black cat in that picture, huh?

00:08:20.772 --> 00:08:22.515 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: It was
just our luck, yeah.

00:08:22.515 --> 00:08:25.140 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What is it about Egypt
that fascinates so many people,

00:08:25.140 --> 00:08:25.670 align:middle line:90%
Mitch?

00:08:25.670 --> 00:08:27.220 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: You know what?
that's an interesting question,

00:08:27.220 --> 00:08:29.370 align:middle line:84%
George, because the
monuments and the symbols

00:08:29.370 --> 00:08:32.340 align:middle line:84%
of ancient Egypt, they have
a magnetic pull on all of us.

00:08:32.340 --> 00:08:35.520 align:middle line:84%
I think these were the
primeval insights of man.

00:08:35.520 --> 00:08:38.580 align:middle line:10%
I think that culture is
older than we've really

00:08:38.580 --> 00:08:42.150 align:middle line:10%
come to understand, and I think
its symbols pull at something

00:08:42.150 --> 00:08:43.559 align:middle line:10%
that's very deep in all of us.

00:08:43.559 --> 00:08:46.037 align:middle line:10%
It's a wish for connection
with higher forces.

00:08:46.037 --> 00:08:48.120 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: We look at the
all-seeing eye on the back

00:08:48.120 --> 00:08:49.440 align:middle line:90%
of money, the pyramid.

00:08:49.440 --> 00:08:49.770 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Yes, sir.

00:08:49.770 --> 00:08:50.760 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: What's that all mean?

00:08:50.760 --> 00:08:52.093 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Isn't it incredible?

00:08:52.093 --> 00:08:53.640 align:middle line:10%
It's a symbol that,
of course, comes

00:08:53.640 --> 00:08:55.380 align:middle line:10%
from ancient Egyptian
civilization,

00:08:55.380 --> 00:08:58.380 align:middle line:10%
but the way it appears on
the back of our currency

00:08:58.380 --> 00:09:00.060 align:middle line:10%
was inspired by Freemasonry.

00:09:00.060 --> 00:09:03.190 align:middle line:10%
And it's surrounded by this
beautiful Latin expression,

00:09:03.190 --> 00:09:05.820 align:middle line:10%
"Annuit Coeptis
Novus Ordo Seclorum."

00:09:05.820 --> 00:09:08.335 align:middle line:10%
God smiles on our new
order of the ages.

00:09:08.335 --> 00:09:09.210 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Interesting.

00:09:09.210 --> 00:09:11.340 align:middle line:84%
There's some meaning here
beyond this, isn't there?

00:09:11.340 --> 00:09:12.300 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Oh, yes.

00:09:12.300 --> 00:09:12.570 align:middle line:90%
It--

00:09:12.570 --> 00:09:14.100 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Is it hidden meaning?

00:09:14.100 --> 00:09:15.975 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: To a degree,
it's hidden meaning.

00:09:15.975 --> 00:09:19.440 align:middle line:10%
The Freemasons believed that
when the American republic was

00:09:19.440 --> 00:09:23.370 align:middle line:10%
being founded, it joined a chain
of ancient civilizations going

00:09:23.370 --> 00:09:26.640 align:middle line:10%
back to Egypt that venerated
the search for meaning.

00:09:26.640 --> 00:09:28.290 align:middle line:10%
And they believe that
was being resumed

00:09:28.290 --> 00:09:30.035 align:middle line:10%
with the founding of America.

00:09:30.035 --> 00:09:32.160 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: With what happened
in ancient Egypt, which

00:09:32.160 --> 00:09:35.190 align:middle line:84%
was thousands of years
ago, these principles

00:09:35.190 --> 00:09:36.310 align:middle line:90%
still apply today.

00:09:36.310 --> 00:09:37.110 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Yeah.

00:09:37.110 --> 00:09:38.818 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How did the
Egyptians know this?

00:09:38.818 --> 00:09:40.720 align:middle line:84%
How did they know the
principles of living?

00:09:40.720 --> 00:09:42.095 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: It's
just incredible.

00:09:42.095 --> 00:09:44.730 align:middle line:10%
They had a much deeper and
richer knowledge of nature

00:09:44.730 --> 00:09:47.100 align:middle line:10%
in the greatest sense
than I think we do.

00:09:47.100 --> 00:09:49.410 align:middle line:10%
And the great principle
of hermetecism

00:09:49.410 --> 00:09:51.210 align:middle line:10%
was as above, so below.

00:09:51.210 --> 00:09:53.130 align:middle line:10%
And they understood
that as individuals we

00:09:53.130 --> 00:09:56.670 align:middle line:10%
are reflections of the cosmos,
and the cosmos reflect us.

00:09:56.670 --> 00:09:57.960 align:middle line:10%
It's all one whole.

00:09:57.960 --> 00:09:59.640 align:middle line:10%
That was their great insight.

00:09:59.640 --> 00:10:01.830 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are there
people today in America

00:10:01.830 --> 00:10:04.577 align:middle line:84%
living and practicing some
of the things of the past?

00:10:04.577 --> 00:10:05.910 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: I believe that's so.

00:10:05.910 --> 00:10:07.110 align:middle line:10%
I believe that's so.

00:10:07.110 --> 00:10:08.670 align:middle line:10%
I think some of
these ideas have been

00:10:08.670 --> 00:10:10.773 align:middle line:10%
preserved within some
of the fraternities

00:10:10.773 --> 00:10:11.940 align:middle line:10%
that we were talking about--

00:10:11.940 --> 00:10:14.070 align:middle line:10%
Rosicrucianism, Freemasonry.

00:10:14.070 --> 00:10:16.140 align:middle line:10%
I believe they appeared
within Manly Hall's work.

00:10:16.140 --> 00:10:18.270 align:middle line:10%
I believe they appeared
within the Kybalion.

00:10:18.270 --> 00:10:21.570 align:middle line:10%
And I think these principles
are not lost to us.

00:10:21.570 --> 00:10:24.600 align:middle line:10%
They have been retained
today in some measure.

00:10:24.600 --> 00:10:28.810 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And how did they
obtain these principles?

00:10:28.810 --> 00:10:32.040 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: There has always
been a sort of very slender,

00:10:32.040 --> 00:10:35.220 align:middle line:10%
thin, golden thread
between modern seekers

00:10:35.220 --> 00:10:36.660 align:middle line:10%
and the thought of the ancients.

00:10:36.660 --> 00:10:40.090 align:middle line:84%
It's been broken, and it has
been lost at various times.

00:10:40.090 --> 00:10:41.940 align:middle line:10%
But some of the
ancient works were

00:10:41.940 --> 00:10:44.370 align:middle line:10%
preserved in writings
that were produced

00:10:44.370 --> 00:10:46.260 align:middle line:10%
in Egypt in late antiquity.

00:10:46.260 --> 00:10:47.880 align:middle line:10%
They were hidden
away in monasteries.

00:10:47.880 --> 00:10:49.950 align:middle line:10%
They resurfaced during
the Renaissance.

00:10:49.950 --> 00:10:53.340 align:middle line:10%
And fortunately, some of this
has come down to us today.

00:10:53.340 --> 00:10:56.550 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Mitch, Egypt has
fascinated and captivated us

00:10:56.550 --> 00:10:58.350 align:middle line:90%
since we have been kids.

00:10:58.350 --> 00:10:59.250 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Yes.

00:10:59.250 --> 00:11:02.040 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: The Great
Pyramids, the Sphinx,

00:11:02.040 --> 00:11:04.380 align:middle line:84%
the knowledge that
they have possessed.

00:11:04.380 --> 00:11:06.360 align:middle line:84%
How advanced were
these people, anyway?

00:11:06.360 --> 00:11:07.860 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: It's
hard for us to say.

00:11:07.860 --> 00:11:11.430 align:middle line:10%
We've only come to understand
the language of hieroglyphs

00:11:11.430 --> 00:11:13.470 align:middle line:10%
really in the past 200 years.

00:11:13.470 --> 00:11:17.080 align:middle line:10%
We're only getting a glimpse
of Egyptian civilization.

00:11:17.080 --> 00:11:18.810 align:middle line:10%
And I think based
on the theories

00:11:18.810 --> 00:11:20.820 align:middle line:10%
of the late John
Anthony West and Robert

00:11:20.820 --> 00:11:22.200 align:middle line:10%
Shock, who you've interviewed--

00:11:22.200 --> 00:11:22.680 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Yes.

00:11:22.680 --> 00:11:24.960 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: --I think
Egyptian civilization is older

00:11:24.960 --> 00:11:26.670 align:middle line:10%
than we've come to understand.

00:11:26.670 --> 00:11:29.190 align:middle line:84%
I think we're just on our knees
looking through a keyhole.

00:11:29.190 --> 00:11:31.167 align:middle line:84%
We've only captured
a tiny glimpse

00:11:31.167 --> 00:11:32.250 align:middle line:90%
of what's really going on.

00:11:32.250 --> 00:11:33.958 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And was it
earthbound knowledge,

00:11:33.958 --> 00:11:36.420 align:middle line:84%
or was it obtained
from up there?

00:11:36.420 --> 00:11:38.170 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: It's
difficult to say, George.

00:11:38.170 --> 00:11:40.290 align:middle line:10%
These people were just
extraordinary figures.

00:11:40.290 --> 00:11:44.160 align:middle line:10%
I haven't researched the
ancient astronaut thesis myself,

00:11:44.160 --> 00:11:46.860 align:middle line:10%
but having worked
with West and Shock,

00:11:46.860 --> 00:11:50.040 align:middle line:10%
I feel certain
that our timeline,

00:11:50.040 --> 00:11:52.890 align:middle line:10%
the traditional
timeline, of Egypt

00:11:52.890 --> 00:11:55.910 align:middle line:10%
does not account for the true
antiquity of that civilization.

00:11:55.910 --> 00:11:56.790 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Remember,
we still don't know

00:11:56.790 --> 00:11:57.840 align:middle line:90%
how they built the pyramids.

00:11:57.840 --> 00:11:58.280 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: No, we don't.

00:11:58.280 --> 00:11:59.530 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: We can't figure it out.

00:11:59.530 --> 00:12:00.738 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: We have theories.

00:12:00.738 --> 00:12:03.660 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Even with incredible
knowledge of architecture

00:12:03.660 --> 00:12:04.540 align:middle line:90%
and building--

00:12:04.540 --> 00:12:04.830 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: That's
exactly correct.

00:12:04.830 --> 00:12:05.940 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: --we can't
really figure it out.

00:12:05.940 --> 00:12:07.660 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: That
is exactly correct.

00:12:07.660 --> 00:12:08.590 align:middle line:10%
We have theories.

00:12:08.590 --> 00:12:09.645 align:middle line:10%
We have certain ideas.

00:12:09.645 --> 00:12:11.520 align:middle line:10%
The same is true for
other ancient monuments,

00:12:11.520 --> 00:12:14.910 align:middle line:10%
like Stonehenge, how the
materials, the raw materials

00:12:14.910 --> 00:12:18.180 align:middle line:10%
for Stonehenge, were moved
across vast distances.

00:12:18.180 --> 00:12:20.250 align:middle line:10%
We have theories, but
we really don't know.

00:12:20.250 --> 00:12:22.800 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Move it, lift it,
get it up there, it's crazy.

00:12:22.800 --> 00:12:24.092 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: We just don't know.

00:12:24.092 --> 00:12:27.160 align:middle line:10%
These civilizations had secrets
that we fully don't understand.

00:12:27.160 --> 00:12:28.320 align:middle line:10%
We have to venerate them.

00:12:28.320 --> 00:12:30.660 align:middle line:10%
We have to fall to our knees
before these civilizations.

00:12:30.660 --> 00:12:33.480 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: If I told you I thought
it was sound resonance, where

00:12:33.480 --> 00:12:38.580 align:middle line:84%
they basically
degravitized these blocks

00:12:38.580 --> 00:12:40.948 align:middle line:84%
and floated them into place,
would you believe that?

00:12:40.948 --> 00:12:42.990 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: Well, I would
say it's an idea that's

00:12:42.990 --> 00:12:43.860 align:middle line:10%
worth considering.

00:12:43.860 --> 00:12:46.380 align:middle line:10%
I take nothing off the
table because the past

00:12:46.380 --> 00:12:51.030 align:middle line:10%
is really shrouded in mystery,
and we owe it our questioning.

00:12:51.030 --> 00:12:52.220 align:middle line:10%
We owe it our study.

00:12:52.220 --> 00:12:53.970 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: When you went
to Egypt, how close

00:12:53.970 --> 00:12:55.140 align:middle line:90%
did you get to the pyramids?

00:12:55.140 --> 00:12:56.010 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Oh, very close.

00:12:56.010 --> 00:12:56.960 align:middle line:90%
Right up, George.

00:12:56.960 --> 00:12:57.560 align:middle line:90%
We went inside--

00:12:57.560 --> 00:12:58.110 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Were you
able to touch the--

00:12:58.110 --> 00:12:59.280 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Oh, absolutely.

00:12:59.280 --> 00:13:02.010 align:middle line:10%
In fact, our director,
Ronnie Thomas, and I

00:13:02.010 --> 00:13:04.320 align:middle line:10%
got to go into temples
that people usually

00:13:04.320 --> 00:13:05.400 align:middle line:10%
don't get to go into.

00:13:05.400 --> 00:13:08.160 align:middle line:10%
There's a temple to the
cat goddess, Sekhmet,

00:13:08.160 --> 00:13:10.440 align:middle line:10%
that we got to enter in Luxor.

00:13:10.440 --> 00:13:13.560 align:middle line:84%
And we did a ceremony,
which was deeply meaningful,

00:13:13.560 --> 00:13:14.510 align:middle line:90%
inside that temple.

00:13:14.510 --> 00:13:16.500 align:middle line:84%
It was pitch black
inside, guarded

00:13:16.500 --> 00:13:18.880 align:middle line:84%
by a soldier with a
machine gun and a guide,

00:13:18.880 --> 00:13:20.260 align:middle line:90%
who brought us inside.

00:13:20.260 --> 00:13:22.030 align:middle line:84%
We got up close and
personal with a lot

00:13:22.030 --> 00:13:23.290 align:middle line:90%
of magnificent material.

00:13:23.290 --> 00:13:25.430 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you feel
spiritual when you're there?

00:13:25.430 --> 00:13:26.230 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Yes.

00:13:26.230 --> 00:13:26.680 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:13:26.680 --> 00:13:27.340 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: It hits you, does it?

00:13:27.340 --> 00:13:28.548 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: Not all the time.

00:13:28.548 --> 00:13:32.170 align:middle line:10%
You know, it's a tough culture
to travel and to shoot film in,

00:13:32.170 --> 00:13:35.920 align:middle line:10%
but there were moments in the
bowels of some of these temples

00:13:35.920 --> 00:13:38.912 align:middle line:10%
where it would be impossible
to be a sensitive person

00:13:38.912 --> 00:13:40.870 align:middle line:10%
and not to feel something
shooting through you.

00:13:40.870 --> 00:13:42.610 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Yeah, you
can just sense it.

00:13:42.610 --> 00:13:42.820 align:middle line:90%
It's there.

00:13:42.820 --> 00:13:43.450 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Magnificent.

00:13:43.450 --> 00:13:44.590 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: My father
was born there.

00:13:44.590 --> 00:13:45.205 align:middle line:90%
We're not Egyptian.

00:13:45.205 --> 00:13:45.760 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Oh, is that right?

00:13:45.760 --> 00:13:47.110 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But that's
where he was born.

00:13:47.110 --> 00:13:48.193 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: How wonderful.

00:13:48.193 --> 00:13:49.870 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And they
left when he was six.

00:13:49.870 --> 00:13:50.670 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: I see.

00:13:50.670 --> 00:13:52.540 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: He's not
with us anymore.

00:13:52.540 --> 00:13:55.570 align:middle line:84%
He always wanted to go
back, and he never did,

00:13:55.570 --> 00:13:59.890 align:middle line:84%
but it fascinated him to
be born in Cairo where

00:13:59.890 --> 00:14:00.820 align:middle line:90%
all this was going on.

00:14:00.820 --> 00:14:02.028 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: It's magnificent.

00:14:02.028 --> 00:14:03.970 align:middle line:10%
You feel something
on a physical scale.

00:14:03.970 --> 00:14:06.040 align:middle line:10%
Life is tough
there, but there are

00:14:06.040 --> 00:14:08.257 align:middle line:10%
moments where you just
enter into a kind of silence

00:14:08.257 --> 00:14:10.090 align:middle line:10%
and you feel something
shooting through you.

00:14:10.090 --> 00:14:12.310 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: And tell us about
the book, "The Kybalion."

00:14:12.310 --> 00:14:15.310 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: "The Kybalion"
came out in 1908.

00:14:15.310 --> 00:14:18.400 align:middle line:10%
That's a book that has long been
considered shrouded in mystery.

00:14:18.400 --> 00:14:22.210 align:middle line:10%
The authorship is attributed
to three initiates,

00:14:22.210 --> 00:14:25.330 align:middle line:10%
three initiates where a
man named William Walker

00:14:25.330 --> 00:14:29.110 align:middle line:10%
Atkinson, who was a brilliant
and prodigious writer

00:14:29.110 --> 00:14:32.150 align:middle line:10%
of new thought in the
early 20th century.

00:14:32.150 --> 00:14:33.490 align:middle line:10%
And he produced the book.

00:14:33.490 --> 00:14:35.320 align:middle line:10%
He later acknowledged
producing the book,

00:14:35.320 --> 00:14:38.650 align:middle line:10%
which is something that we
talk about in the documentary.

00:14:38.650 --> 00:14:42.760 align:middle line:10%
And he really created a
compendium, as best we have it,

00:14:42.760 --> 00:14:46.400 align:middle line:10%
of ancient Greek Egyptian
spiritual psychology.

00:14:46.400 --> 00:14:47.200 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Aha.

00:14:47.200 --> 00:14:49.120 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: It's a book
with seven principles.

00:14:49.120 --> 00:14:50.870 align:middle line:90%
They are straightforward.

00:14:50.870 --> 00:14:52.690 align:middle line:90%
They are applicable to life.

00:14:52.690 --> 00:14:55.510 align:middle line:84%
And knowing who the author
was doesn't do anything

00:14:55.510 --> 00:14:57.220 align:middle line:84%
to reduce the
mystery of the book

00:14:57.220 --> 00:15:00.713 align:middle line:84%
because he's really dealing with
material that goes back ages.

00:15:00.713 --> 00:15:01.630 align:middle line:90%
It's a wonderful book.

00:15:01.630 --> 00:15:03.040 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What are some
of the principles?

00:15:03.040 --> 00:15:05.123 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: One of the
core principles of the book

00:15:05.123 --> 00:15:07.240 align:middle line:10%
is that everything that
goes on in the world

00:15:07.240 --> 00:15:08.620 align:middle line:10%
is a kind of polarity.

00:15:08.620 --> 00:15:10.063 align:middle line:10%
Again, as above, so below.

00:15:10.063 --> 00:15:11.480 align:middle line:10%
So that when you're
experiencing--

00:15:11.480 --> 00:15:12.220 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Yin and yang.

00:15:12.220 --> 00:15:13.480 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: Yes,
yin and yang, that's

00:15:13.480 --> 00:15:14.605 align:middle line:10%
another way of putting it.

00:15:14.605 --> 00:15:18.130 align:middle line:10%
So and this polarity exists
within our psychology as well,

00:15:18.130 --> 00:15:20.770 align:middle line:10%
so that you can actually
reverse negative emotions

00:15:20.770 --> 00:15:22.600 align:middle line:10%
and turn them into
positive ones,

00:15:22.600 --> 00:15:25.090 align:middle line:10%
as long as you can
identify their opposite.

00:15:25.090 --> 00:15:29.950 align:middle line:10%
So fear can turn into bravery.

00:15:29.950 --> 00:15:33.820 align:middle line:10%
Depression can turn
into enthusiasm.

00:15:33.820 --> 00:15:36.430 align:middle line:10%
Ennui or a state
of low energy can

00:15:36.430 --> 00:15:38.530 align:middle line:10%
turn into boundless passion.

00:15:38.530 --> 00:15:40.002 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Anxiety
into opportunity.

00:15:40.002 --> 00:15:40.960 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Absolutely.

00:15:40.960 --> 00:15:41.830 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:15:41.830 --> 00:15:44.020 align:middle line:10%
We are part of a sliding
scale, and if you

00:15:44.020 --> 00:15:46.540 align:middle line:10%
can identify where
you are on that scale

00:15:46.540 --> 00:15:50.682 align:middle line:10%
through an act of mental
expression, mental wish,

00:15:50.682 --> 00:15:52.890 align:middle line:10%
you can actually slide to
the other end of the scale.

00:15:52.890 --> 00:15:54.265 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: To a
person like you who

00:15:54.265 --> 00:15:56.890 align:middle line:84%
is exposed to this
on a regular basis,

00:15:56.890 --> 00:15:58.772 align:middle line:84%
has it changed your
views on anything?

00:15:58.772 --> 00:15:59.980 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: Without question.

00:15:59.980 --> 00:16:02.970 align:middle line:10%
You know, George, several years
ago, I wrote off "The Kybalion"

00:16:02.970 --> 00:16:06.610 align:middle line:10%
as just being a kind of novelty
of early 20th century cultism.

00:16:06.610 --> 00:16:09.590 align:middle line:10%
And then I get back on the
scent trail of the book.

00:16:09.590 --> 00:16:12.730 align:middle line:10%
And there was one summer where
I read it five times in a row,

00:16:12.730 --> 00:16:14.530 align:middle line:10%
and it really
transformed my search.

00:16:14.530 --> 00:16:16.540 align:middle line:84%
I felt so moved
and touched by it.

00:16:16.540 --> 00:16:20.110 align:middle line:10%
I realized this book
really did contain threads

00:16:20.110 --> 00:16:21.510 align:middle line:10%
of the wisdom of the ancients.

00:16:21.510 --> 00:16:23.450 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It sounds like
the more you read it,

00:16:23.450 --> 00:16:25.300 align:middle line:84%
the more information
you get from it.

00:16:25.300 --> 00:16:26.290 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: Precisely.

00:16:26.290 --> 00:16:29.210 align:middle line:10%
Because although there are a
lot of practical insights in it,

00:16:29.210 --> 00:16:31.750 align:middle line:10%
the author said that he didn't
want to give you the methods.

00:16:31.750 --> 00:16:35.740 align:middle line:10%
Through experiment, you had to
arrive at the methods yourself.

00:16:35.740 --> 00:16:37.600 align:middle line:84%
Because only then
would you really

00:16:37.600 --> 00:16:39.790 align:middle line:84%
come into understanding
them and applying them.

00:16:39.790 --> 00:16:41.688 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What does the
title "Kybalion" mean?

00:16:41.688 --> 00:16:42.730 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: No one knows.

00:16:42.730 --> 00:16:43.720 align:middle line:90%
No one knows.

00:16:43.720 --> 00:16:44.520 align:middle line:90%
It's sort of a--

00:16:44.520 --> 00:16:46.145 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It's not
tied to the Kabbalah?

00:16:46.145 --> 00:16:48.370 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: No, it's not
tied to Kabbalah precisely.

00:16:48.370 --> 00:16:50.900 align:middle line:10%
There's no mention of
Kabbalah in the book.

00:16:50.900 --> 00:16:54.140 align:middle line:10%
It seems to be a Helenized
version of Kabbalah,

00:16:54.140 --> 00:16:56.850 align:middle line:10%
but he never explains
the meaning of the title,

00:16:56.850 --> 00:16:58.210 align:middle line:10%
so another mystery.

00:16:58.210 --> 00:17:01.540 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Now, with this
mystery, of course, what

00:17:01.540 --> 00:17:03.910 align:middle line:10%
happened to him, the author?

00:17:03.910 --> 00:17:04.810 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: Oh, gosh.

00:17:04.810 --> 00:17:06.550 align:middle line:10%
He was an extraordinary figure.

00:17:06.550 --> 00:17:10.660 align:middle line:10%
He produced dozens and dozens of
books in the early 20th century

00:17:10.660 --> 00:17:14.345 align:middle line:10%
under pseudonyms like Yogi
Ramacharaka, Magus Incognito--

00:17:14.345 --> 00:17:15.970 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Why did they
hide their names?

00:17:15.970 --> 00:17:17.387 align:middle line:10%
Because they could
get in trouble?

00:17:17.387 --> 00:17:19.890 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: Well, sometimes
he liked to dramatize things.

00:17:19.890 --> 00:17:22.030 align:middle line:10%
You know, the man
just literally wrote

00:17:22.030 --> 00:17:25.390 align:middle line:10%
dozens of books under his own
publishing company in Chicago

00:17:25.390 --> 00:17:27.359 align:middle line:10%
called the Yogi
Publication Society.

00:17:27.359 --> 00:17:28.180 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yogi.

00:17:28.180 --> 00:17:28.980 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Yeah.

00:17:28.980 --> 00:17:30.730 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes he would
use other names.

00:17:30.730 --> 00:17:32.560 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes he would
use French names.

00:17:32.560 --> 00:17:35.320 align:middle line:84%
Like, one of his names
was Theron Q. Dumont.

00:17:35.320 --> 00:17:37.970 align:middle line:10%
And I think he felt it would
give the books greater gravity

00:17:37.970 --> 00:17:40.540 align:middle line:10%
if they seemed to be coming
from the pen of other people.

00:17:40.540 --> 00:17:43.600 align:middle line:10%
I think he felt that people
wouldn't believe one man could

00:17:43.600 --> 00:17:44.880 align:middle line:10%
have produced all these books.

00:17:44.880 --> 00:17:46.380 align:middle line:10%
He was a little bit
like Manly Hall.

00:17:46.380 --> 00:17:48.040 align:middle line:10%
His output was incredible.

00:17:48.040 --> 00:17:49.917 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Maybe he was
a marketing expert.

00:17:49.917 --> 00:17:52.000 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: Well, he was
that, among other things.

00:17:52.000 --> 00:17:52.850 align:middle line:90%
He was a lawyer.

00:17:52.850 --> 00:17:54.400 align:middle line:90%
He was a marketing expert.

00:17:54.400 --> 00:17:57.790 align:middle line:10%
He had a flair for drama,
but he was totally sincere.

00:17:57.790 --> 00:18:00.700 align:middle line:10%
And he really was one of
the greatest interpreters

00:18:00.700 --> 00:18:02.790 align:middle line:10%
of new thought or
mind metaphysics.

00:18:02.790 --> 00:18:05.980 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Now through all of
these esoteric principles

00:18:05.980 --> 00:18:08.230 align:middle line:84%
that you have
investigated, are there

00:18:08.230 --> 00:18:10.360 align:middle line:90%
mysteries behind them, Mitch?

00:18:10.360 --> 00:18:13.840 align:middle line:84%
And what I mean by
that are mysteries

00:18:13.840 --> 00:18:17.610 align:middle line:84%
that were intertwined
where we had to figure out

00:18:17.610 --> 00:18:18.447 align:middle line:90%
what the puzzle was?

00:18:18.447 --> 00:18:19.780 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: There's no question.

00:18:19.780 --> 00:18:21.510 align:middle line:10%
In fact, I think we're
living with a great mystery

00:18:21.510 --> 00:18:23.130 align:middle line:10%
right now in our
generation, which

00:18:23.130 --> 00:18:27.810 align:middle line:10%
is if our minds are causative,
if our thoughts make things

00:18:27.810 --> 00:18:30.180 align:middle line:10%
happen, and I
believe they do, why?

00:18:30.180 --> 00:18:32.183 align:middle line:10%
Why should there be
any effect at all?

00:18:32.183 --> 00:18:34.600 align:middle line:10%
And I try to go through some
of this in "The Miracle Club"

00:18:34.600 --> 00:18:36.930 align:middle line:10%
and at least come up
with a theory of why

00:18:36.930 --> 00:18:38.370 align:middle line:10%
our thoughts are causative.

00:18:38.370 --> 00:18:40.560 align:middle line:10%
I believe that
everything is going on

00:18:40.560 --> 00:18:43.050 align:middle line:10%
at once, that everything
is in superposition.

00:18:43.050 --> 00:18:46.890 align:middle line:10%
And we select things or localize
things through our perceptions,

00:18:46.890 --> 00:18:47.970 align:middle line:10%
through our focus.

00:18:47.970 --> 00:18:49.830 align:middle line:84%
I don't believe we live
in the linear world

00:18:49.830 --> 00:18:52.800 align:middle line:84%
that we detect around us, but
that something more dynamic

00:18:52.800 --> 00:18:54.930 align:middle line:84%
is happening, which
is why we have so much

00:18:54.930 --> 00:18:58.950 align:middle line:84%
testimony of our thoughts
seeming to contribute

00:18:58.950 --> 00:19:00.000 align:middle line:90%
to what really happens.

00:19:00.000 --> 00:19:01.740 align:middle line:84%
I think they actually
do, and we have

00:19:01.740 --> 00:19:04.080 align:middle line:84%
to start trying to grapple,
at least in our time,

00:19:04.080 --> 00:19:04.900 align:middle line:90%
with why that is.

00:19:04.900 --> 00:19:05.700 align:middle line:90%
That's a mystery.

00:19:05.700 --> 00:19:07.290 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What is the
Midnight Archive?

00:19:07.290 --> 00:19:08.790 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: Oh, the
Midnight Archive

00:19:08.790 --> 00:19:13.020 align:middle line:84%
is a wonderful online
series about people

00:19:13.020 --> 00:19:15.270 align:middle line:90%
who explore strange phenomena.

00:19:15.270 --> 00:19:17.250 align:middle line:10%
It's directed by my
friend Ronnie Thomas.

00:19:17.250 --> 00:19:20.430 align:middle line:10%
And Ronnie and I've done several
episodes on the Ouija board

00:19:20.430 --> 00:19:21.230 align:middle line:10%
and on occult--

00:19:21.230 --> 00:19:22.990 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Oh, stay away
from Ouija boards.

00:19:22.990 --> 00:19:23.790 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: Yeah.

00:19:23.790 --> 00:19:25.650 align:middle line:10%
I've softened on the
question, George.

00:19:25.650 --> 00:19:26.920 align:middle line:10%
I've softened on the question.

00:19:26.920 --> 00:19:29.170 align:middle line:10%
I won't discourage anybody
from experimenting.

00:19:29.170 --> 00:19:31.800 align:middle line:10%
I know there are fearsome
stories around Ouija,

00:19:31.800 --> 00:19:33.232 align:middle line:10%
and I don't downplay
any of that.

00:19:33.232 --> 00:19:35.190 align:middle line:10%
But there have been
wonderful discoveries, too,

00:19:35.190 --> 00:19:37.200 align:middle line:10%
and I don't want to stifle
anybody's experience.

00:19:37.200 --> 00:19:39.180 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, you actually
talked about the Ouija board

00:19:39.180 --> 00:19:40.230 align:middle line:90%
on Midnight Archive.

00:19:40.230 --> 00:19:41.652 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Oh, for real.

00:19:41.652 --> 00:19:43.110 align:middle line:10%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:19:43.110 --> 00:19:46.680 align:middle line:84%
>> The earliest aspect of the
spiritualist experience was

00:19:46.680 --> 00:19:50.610 align:middle line:84%
the sance, people joining hands
around a table in a darkened

00:19:50.610 --> 00:19:53.190 align:middle line:84%
parlor and a medium,
usually a woman,

00:19:53.190 --> 00:19:55.720 align:middle line:84%
who would go into a
kind of trance state,

00:19:55.720 --> 00:19:58.440 align:middle line:84%
and spirits would
speak through her.

00:19:58.440 --> 00:20:00.960 align:middle line:84%
But Americans went in
search of technologies

00:20:00.960 --> 00:20:03.300 align:middle line:84%
to make the whole
experience easier

00:20:03.300 --> 00:20:05.820 align:middle line:84%
and to find a way of
doing it themselves,

00:20:05.820 --> 00:20:07.518 align:middle line:90%
to dispense with the medium.

00:20:07.518 --> 00:20:09.060 align:middle line:84%
One of the things
people would engage

00:20:09.060 --> 00:20:11.590 align:middle line:84%
in would be what became
known as automatic writing.

00:20:11.590 --> 00:20:14.970 align:middle line:84%
Somebody would simply hold
a quill in his or her hand

00:20:14.970 --> 00:20:17.340 align:middle line:84%
and attempt to go
into a trance state

00:20:17.340 --> 00:20:19.500 align:middle line:84%
and write some message
from the afterworld.

00:20:19.500 --> 00:20:21.610 align:middle line:84%
But that was unsatisfying
to a lot of people,

00:20:21.610 --> 00:20:23.310 align:middle line:84%
because it produced
page after page

00:20:23.310 --> 00:20:25.290 align:middle line:90%
of very meandering writing.

00:20:25.290 --> 00:20:27.390 align:middle line:84%
The French came up with
an interesting innovation

00:20:27.390 --> 00:20:29.130 align:middle line:84%
of their own called
the planchette,

00:20:29.130 --> 00:20:33.600 align:middle line:84%
which would allow people, either
individually or in groups,

00:20:33.600 --> 00:20:35.820 align:middle line:84%
to take a kind of
little plank, which

00:20:35.820 --> 00:20:38.670 align:middle line:84%
looks a great deal like a
little plank that revolves

00:20:38.670 --> 00:20:40.380 align:middle line:90%
around the Ouija board today.

00:20:40.380 --> 00:20:42.690 align:middle line:84%
Only what the French
did was design

00:20:42.690 --> 00:20:47.140 align:middle line:84%
a little board that was made of
wood that was on ball bearings.

00:20:47.140 --> 00:20:49.290 align:middle line:84%
And in the center
of the planchette,

00:20:49.290 --> 00:20:51.930 align:middle line:84%
they had a hole where you
could insert a pencil.

00:20:51.930 --> 00:20:54.173 align:middle line:84%
And it would slide around
and write out messages

00:20:54.173 --> 00:20:55.090 align:middle line:90%
from the spirit world.

00:20:55.090 --> 00:20:58.000 align:middle line:84%
It was supposed to be easier
than automatic writing.

00:20:58.000 --> 00:21:00.780 align:middle line:90%
But again, it could be tedious.

00:21:00.780 --> 00:21:02.340 align:middle line:90%
It could be time consuming.

00:21:02.340 --> 00:21:04.890 align:middle line:84%
And people seemed to feel
it produced page after page

00:21:04.890 --> 00:21:06.210 align:middle line:90%
of barely intelligible writing.

00:21:06.210 --> 00:21:09.210 align:middle line:84%
So along came the
American engineers,

00:21:09.210 --> 00:21:11.130 align:middle line:84%
and they created
all kinds of things

00:21:11.130 --> 00:21:13.547 align:middle line:84%
with different pulleys,
and devices, and weights.

00:21:13.547 --> 00:21:15.880 align:middle line:84%
When you look at the blueprints
of some of these things,

00:21:15.880 --> 00:21:18.330 align:middle line:84%
you'll find it hard
to imagine that people

00:21:18.330 --> 00:21:22.350 align:middle line:84%
felt that these objects could
have made anything much easier.

00:21:22.350 --> 00:21:25.050 align:middle line:84%
Now, there was another
development happening.

00:21:25.050 --> 00:21:28.350 align:middle line:84%
It was much simpler than
this whole wide array

00:21:28.350 --> 00:21:30.510 align:middle line:90%
of spiritual telegraph devices.

00:21:30.510 --> 00:21:33.480 align:middle line:84%
And it was something that
was sometimes used at sances

00:21:33.480 --> 00:21:35.310 align:middle line:90%
called the alphabet board.

00:21:35.310 --> 00:21:37.980 align:middle line:84%
It was just a very simple
board with the letters

00:21:37.980 --> 00:21:40.260 align:middle line:84%
of the alphabet
printed out on it.

00:21:40.260 --> 00:21:44.640 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes a medium would
point to a certain letter,

00:21:44.640 --> 00:21:47.640 align:middle line:84%
and upon pointing to a
letter, if she received

00:21:47.640 --> 00:21:50.280 align:middle line:84%
[KNOCKING] a spirit knock
or some sort of symbol

00:21:50.280 --> 00:21:52.530 align:middle line:84%
from the other
world, that system

00:21:52.530 --> 00:21:56.220 align:middle line:84%
would be used almost as
an occult telegraph system

00:21:56.220 --> 00:21:58.110 align:middle line:90%
to spell out words.

00:21:58.110 --> 00:22:01.050 align:middle line:84%
Somewhere along the line,
a group of spiritualists

00:22:01.050 --> 00:22:04.740 align:middle line:84%
got the idea that you could
take all these innovations

00:22:04.740 --> 00:22:08.130 align:middle line:84%
and unite them into one
beautiful, simple, small

00:22:08.130 --> 00:22:11.010 align:middle line:84%
object, and that was
the talking board.

00:22:11.010 --> 00:22:12.990 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't until
several years later

00:22:12.990 --> 00:22:15.420 align:middle line:84%
that a group of
novelty manufacturers

00:22:15.420 --> 00:22:18.840 align:middle line:84%
in the city of Baltimore got
together and put a patent

00:22:18.840 --> 00:22:19.790 align:middle line:90%
on this object.

00:22:19.790 --> 00:22:22.740 align:middle line:84%
And Ouija began to be marketed
as a commercial object,

00:22:22.740 --> 00:22:24.510 align:middle line:90%
as a toy, as a novelty.

00:22:24.510 --> 00:22:26.880 align:middle line:84%
My contention is
actually that Ouija never

00:22:26.880 --> 00:22:30.270 align:middle line:84%
should have been able to
gain a patent in any case

00:22:30.270 --> 00:22:32.880 align:middle line:84%
because patents are supposed
to be for inventions, not

00:22:32.880 --> 00:22:33.840 align:middle line:90%
for discoveries.

00:22:33.840 --> 00:22:34.740 align:middle line:90%
[END PLAYBACK]

00:22:34.740 --> 00:22:36.532 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you use a
Ouija board yourself?

00:22:36.532 --> 00:22:38.670 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: I have
used a Ouija board.

00:22:38.670 --> 00:22:40.140 align:middle line:90%
Had some scary things happen.

00:22:40.140 --> 00:22:40.560 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Uh-huh.

00:22:40.560 --> 00:22:41.475 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: Some
unusual things happen.

00:22:41.475 --> 00:22:42.750 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It opens up a portal.

00:22:42.750 --> 00:22:44.125 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: It
opens up a portal.

00:22:44.125 --> 00:22:47.640 align:middle line:10%
And I once was doing an online
sance with a group of people

00:22:47.640 --> 00:22:49.470 align:middle line:10%
at a website called Elite Daily.

00:22:49.470 --> 00:22:51.030 align:middle line:10%
It's a fashion website.

00:22:51.030 --> 00:22:53.940 align:middle line:10%
And we got the name
and the death date

00:22:53.940 --> 00:22:57.720 align:middle line:10%
of a woman who later turned
out to be a journalist, who

00:22:57.720 --> 00:23:00.900 align:middle line:10%
had lived on that very
block and committed suicide.

00:23:00.900 --> 00:23:02.070 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: See, it happens.

00:23:02.070 --> 00:23:03.270 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: It happens.

00:23:03.270 --> 00:23:05.080 align:middle line:84%
Strange things happen
with the Ouija board.

00:23:05.080 --> 00:23:07.650 align:middle line:10%
And I know there are
a lot scary stories,

00:23:07.650 --> 00:23:09.935 align:middle line:10%
but I also believe
in experimentation.

00:23:09.935 --> 00:23:11.560 align:middle line:10%
And I don't want to
discourage anybody.

00:23:11.560 --> 00:23:13.860 align:middle line:10%
I just want them to have their
eyes open when they do it.

00:23:13.860 --> 00:23:15.902 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: We have a friend
named Karen Doleman who

00:23:15.902 --> 00:23:17.170 align:middle line:90%
loves the Ouija board.

00:23:17.170 --> 00:23:18.330 align:middle line:90%
She swears by it.

00:23:18.330 --> 00:23:20.950 align:middle line:84%
And she thinks it's
the individual, not

00:23:20.950 --> 00:23:24.160 align:middle line:84%
the board, that creates these
kinds of problems and issues.

00:23:24.160 --> 00:23:27.640 align:middle line:84%
All I know is back in my
St. Louis broadcast days,

00:23:27.640 --> 00:23:29.690 align:middle line:84%
I had a Ouija board
in the studio.

00:23:29.690 --> 00:23:30.490 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Wow.

00:23:30.490 --> 00:23:32.800 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Everything went wrong.

00:23:32.800 --> 00:23:35.480 align:middle line:84%
Nothing ever went wrong,
but things went wrong.

