>>HOROWITZ: Interesting.

00:23:36.480 --> 00:23:38.770 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: My commercial
computer went out.

00:23:38.770 --> 00:23:40.420 align:middle line:90%
We couldn't run commercials.

00:23:40.420 --> 00:23:44.440 align:middle line:84%
The board that you control your
audio, the lights would go out.

00:23:44.440 --> 00:23:46.600 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't know who
was on and who wasn't.

00:23:46.600 --> 00:23:47.680 align:middle line:90%
It was awful.

00:23:47.680 --> 00:23:49.450 align:middle line:90%
I told my producer at the time--

00:23:49.450 --> 00:23:52.960 align:middle line:84%
I said, Howard, get this thing
out of here and get it out now.

00:23:52.960 --> 00:23:56.080 align:middle line:84%
So he took it out,
walked down the hallway.

00:23:56.080 --> 00:23:57.407 align:middle line:90%
Everything went back on.

00:23:57.407 --> 00:23:58.490 align:middle line:90%
Computers started working.

00:23:58.490 --> 00:23:59.110 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Interesting.

00:23:59.110 --> 00:24:00.193 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: The board worked.

00:24:00.193 --> 00:24:02.490 align:middle line:84%
But he gave the Ouija board
to one of our news guys,

00:24:02.490 --> 00:24:04.120 align:middle line:90%
a fellow by the name of Darryl.

00:24:04.120 --> 00:24:05.255 align:middle line:90%
Gave it to him as a gift.

00:24:05.255 --> 00:24:06.130 align:middle line:90%
He said, you take it.

00:24:06.130 --> 00:24:07.510 align:middle line:90%
He said, OK, great.

00:24:07.510 --> 00:24:10.030 align:middle line:90%
The next day, Darryl gets fired.

00:24:10.030 --> 00:24:12.550 align:middle line:84%
We run into him about
two weeks later.

00:24:12.550 --> 00:24:14.650 align:middle line:84%
And we're saying, god,
Darryl, how are you doing?

00:24:14.650 --> 00:24:16.180 align:middle line:90%
Sorry about what happened.

00:24:16.180 --> 00:24:17.710 align:middle line:90%
He said, you know what?

00:24:17.710 --> 00:24:21.130 align:middle line:84%
Ever since I had that
Ouija board from you guys,

00:24:21.130 --> 00:24:23.770 align:middle line:90%
my life has been in the tubes.

00:24:23.770 --> 00:24:26.410 align:middle line:84%
He said, not only
did I get fired,

00:24:26.410 --> 00:24:29.920 align:middle line:84%
but two days later, my
girlfriend dumped me.

00:24:29.920 --> 00:24:31.960 align:middle line:84%
I threw away the Ouija
board, and things started

00:24:31.960 --> 00:24:33.190 align:middle line:90%
getting better for me again.

00:24:33.190 --> 00:24:34.460 align:middle line:90%
How do you explain that?

00:24:34.460 --> 00:24:35.530 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: Well,
it's very strange.

00:24:35.530 --> 00:24:36.970 align:middle line:84%
I'm glad he threw
the Ouija board away.

00:24:36.970 --> 00:24:38.200 align:middle line:84%
I was worried you were
going to present it

00:24:38.200 --> 00:24:39.730 align:middle line:90%
to me as a gift after the show.

00:24:39.730 --> 00:24:40.570 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Maybe.

00:24:40.570 --> 00:24:42.000 align:middle line:90%
You never know what I've got.

00:24:42.000 --> 00:24:44.500 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: I wanted
to breathe easier.

00:24:44.500 --> 00:24:45.550 align:middle line:10%
It's strange, George.

00:24:45.550 --> 00:24:47.760 align:middle line:10%
It is an object that
attracts unusual energy,

00:24:47.760 --> 00:24:50.010 align:middle line:10%
and some people, like the
friend you were referencing,

00:24:50.010 --> 00:24:52.510 align:middle line:10%
theorize that it's kind
of an invisible line

00:24:52.510 --> 00:24:54.730 align:middle line:10%
to our own psyche and
our own subconscious.

00:24:54.730 --> 00:24:57.100 align:middle line:10%
But even if that's true,
what kinds of things

00:24:57.100 --> 00:24:59.920 align:middle line:10%
are lurking in our psyche
and our subconscious

00:24:59.920 --> 00:25:01.630 align:middle line:10%
if this is what's
coming out of it?

00:25:01.630 --> 00:25:03.130 align:middle line:10%
It's a very strange object.

00:25:03.130 --> 00:25:04.990 align:middle line:10%
And when I was
growing up, as a kid,

00:25:04.990 --> 00:25:07.450 align:middle line:10%
I wasn't so sure if there were
any occult properties to it.

00:25:07.450 --> 00:25:09.610 align:middle line:10%
Because I thought, look,
it's got a bar code.

00:25:09.610 --> 00:25:10.510 align:middle line:10%
It's in shrink wrap.

00:25:10.510 --> 00:25:11.800 align:middle line:10%
It's at the toy store.

00:25:11.800 --> 00:25:12.910 align:middle line:10%
It doesn't matter.

00:25:12.910 --> 00:25:15.980 align:middle line:84%
Wherever you get it from, it
has some very potent and strange

00:25:15.980 --> 00:25:16.780 align:middle line:90%
properties.

00:25:16.780 --> 00:25:18.730 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, our
agents obviously

00:25:18.730 --> 00:25:20.868 align:middle line:84%
were into all kinds of
metaphysical things.

00:25:20.868 --> 00:25:21.910 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Oh, for sure.

00:25:21.910 --> 00:25:22.480 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Weren't they?

00:25:22.480 --> 00:25:23.000 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Yeah.

00:25:23.000 --> 00:25:25.370 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What got them so
turned on by all this stuff?

00:25:25.370 --> 00:25:28.570 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: They believed that
every aspect of life was sacred

00:25:28.570 --> 00:25:30.670 align:middle line:10%
and that everything
that was going on

00:25:30.670 --> 00:25:31.950 align:middle line:10%
was part of a continuum.

00:25:31.950 --> 00:25:35.140 align:middle line:10%
So if you could freeze in
time a certain moment--

00:25:35.140 --> 00:25:36.910 align:middle line:10%
maybe you're using
a divinatory method,

00:25:36.910 --> 00:25:39.880 align:middle line:10%
like the I Ching or tarot
cards, or something else,

00:25:39.880 --> 00:25:41.080 align:middle line:10%
or the stars--

00:25:41.080 --> 00:25:43.172 align:middle line:10%
if you could freeze in
time a certain moment,

00:25:43.172 --> 00:25:45.130 align:middle line:10%
they believed that you
might be able to discern

00:25:45.130 --> 00:25:48.430 align:middle line:10%
everything else that's going
on, past, present, future.

00:25:48.430 --> 00:25:51.520 align:middle line:84%
Everything is like a three
dimensional photograph of life.

00:25:51.520 --> 00:25:53.500 align:middle line:84%
And in that sense,
you could use almost

00:25:53.500 --> 00:25:58.420 align:middle line:84%
any pictogrammatic device
for foresight for prophecy.

00:25:58.420 --> 00:26:01.960 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did they not have any
bad experiences with the Ouija

00:26:01.960 --> 00:26:04.212 align:middle line:84%
board, or the talking board,
as they called it then?

00:26:04.212 --> 00:26:05.170 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Sure, sure.

00:26:05.170 --> 00:26:08.150 align:middle line:10%
Look, I think people had lots
of good and bad experiences,

00:26:08.150 --> 00:26:11.500 align:middle line:10%
but we are so hungry to touch
something beyond the physical,

00:26:11.500 --> 00:26:13.540 align:middle line:10%
beyond flesh and
bone, that I think

00:26:13.540 --> 00:26:16.600 align:middle line:10%
we're very attached to anything
that seems to be a kind of line

00:26:16.600 --> 00:26:18.072 align:middle line:10%
of communication to the unseen.

00:26:18.072 --> 00:26:20.530 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: And it looks like it
was the French who brought us

00:26:20.530 --> 00:26:21.360 align:middle line:10%
the planchette, the--

00:26:21.360 --> 00:26:23.402 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: The French
brought us the planchette,

00:26:23.402 --> 00:26:26.080 align:middle line:10%
but it was good, old
do-it-yourself Americans who

00:26:26.080 --> 00:26:29.680 align:middle line:10%
created the alphabet board and
finally took this French device

00:26:29.680 --> 00:26:31.750 align:middle line:10%
and figured out how
to apply it in a way

00:26:31.750 --> 00:26:33.530 align:middle line:10%
that everybody could understand.

00:26:33.530 --> 00:26:34.600 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Now the
Ouija board is still

00:26:34.600 --> 00:26:36.683 align:middle line:10%
being sold as a game by
Parker Brothers, isn't it?

00:26:36.683 --> 00:26:37.790 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Oh, for real.

00:26:37.790 --> 00:26:39.220 align:middle line:84%
And for a long time,
Parker Brothers

00:26:39.220 --> 00:26:40.428 align:middle line:90%
didn't want to talk about it.

00:26:40.428 --> 00:26:43.960 align:middle line:10%
When I wrote my first article
on Ouija years ago, actually

00:26:43.960 --> 00:26:46.000 align:middle line:10%
the public relations
person of Parker Brothers

00:26:46.000 --> 00:26:47.330 align:middle line:10%
wouldn't get back to me.

00:26:47.330 --> 00:26:50.915 align:middle line:10%
So I wrote a letter directly to
the president of the company.

00:26:50.915 --> 00:26:52.540 align:middle line:10%
And I said, look,
I'm just a guy trying

00:26:52.540 --> 00:26:55.030 align:middle line:10%
to write an article about
this cultural artifact,

00:26:55.030 --> 00:26:57.310 align:middle line:10%
and your PR people
won't respond to me.

00:26:57.310 --> 00:26:59.850 align:middle line:10%
Two days later, I heard
from the vice president

00:26:59.850 --> 00:27:01.408 align:middle line:10%
to PR, who did get back to me.

00:27:01.408 --> 00:27:03.700 align:middle line:10%
But for a long time, they
didn't want to talk about it.

00:27:03.700 --> 00:27:05.742 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It was a big
seller for them, wasn't it?

00:27:05.742 --> 00:27:06.640 align:middle line:90%
Probably still is.

00:27:06.640 --> 00:27:07.900 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: It is nowadays.

00:27:07.900 --> 00:27:09.430 align:middle line:84%
It was a big seller
for many years.

00:27:09.430 --> 00:27:10.610 align:middle line:90%
Then it sort of fell off.

00:27:10.610 --> 00:27:12.850 align:middle line:10%
And I think they got
worried about the board's

00:27:12.850 --> 00:27:14.230 align:middle line:10%
sinister associations.

00:27:14.230 --> 00:27:16.670 align:middle line:10%
They got worried about
boycotts and things like that.

00:27:16.670 --> 00:27:19.120 align:middle line:10%
But then they licensed
it to the movies,

00:27:19.120 --> 00:27:21.495 align:middle line:10%
and these fairly successful
Ouija horror movies came out.

00:27:21.495 --> 00:27:23.828 align:middle line:10%
Now they're in love with the
Ouija board all over again.

00:27:23.828 --> 00:27:26.420 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I will admit that I
bought one a long time ago.

00:27:26.420 --> 00:27:27.250 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Yeah.

00:27:27.250 --> 00:27:29.200 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I don't think
I've ever used it.

00:27:29.200 --> 00:27:31.790 align:middle line:84%
I don't even know
where it is anymore.

00:27:31.790 --> 00:27:33.498 align:middle line:84%
I hope it's not in my
basement somewhere.

00:27:33.498 --> 00:27:34.298 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Right.

00:27:34.298 --> 00:27:35.460 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: But I did buy one.

00:27:35.460 --> 00:27:36.260 align:middle line:90%
I did buy one.

00:27:36.260 --> 00:27:38.470 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: Yeah, I have a
couple of antique boards.

00:27:38.470 --> 00:27:40.040 align:middle line:10%
I gave one away to
a friend recently.

00:27:40.040 --> 00:27:40.840 align:middle line:10%
I keep another--

00:27:40.840 --> 00:27:43.230 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Nice guy.

00:27:43.230 --> 00:27:44.813 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: Hopefully
he'll remain so.

00:27:44.813 --> 00:27:47.830 align:middle line:10%
And I do use it.

00:27:47.830 --> 00:27:50.552 align:middle line:10%
I do bring it out when friends
or guests want to use it,

00:27:50.552 --> 00:27:51.760 align:middle line:10%
but I don't use it regularly.

00:27:51.760 --> 00:27:53.170 align:middle line:10%
I keep it up in my closet.

00:27:53.170 --> 00:27:55.340 align:middle line:10%
It's not something I
toy around with lightly.

00:27:55.340 --> 00:27:57.340 align:middle line:84%
I mean, this is not
something that I play around

00:27:57.340 --> 00:27:59.260 align:middle line:84%
with like a magic 8
ball or something.

00:27:59.260 --> 00:28:01.840 align:middle line:84%
I do take it seriously, and
I keep the antique board.

00:28:01.840 --> 00:28:03.255 align:middle line:90%
That's my one and only.

00:28:03.255 --> 00:28:05.380 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Let's talk about
sances if we can, Mitch.

00:28:05.380 --> 00:28:06.310 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Yes, sir.

00:28:06.310 --> 00:28:08.345 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They were
big back in the 1800s.

00:28:08.345 --> 00:28:09.220 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Oh, yeah.

00:28:09.220 --> 00:28:10.887 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They're
probably still big now.

00:28:10.887 --> 00:28:12.130 align:middle line:90%
What are they?

00:28:12.130 --> 00:28:14.860 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: Sances simply
involve a group of people

00:28:14.860 --> 00:28:17.800 align:middle line:10%
joining hands or touching
fingers around a table

00:28:17.800 --> 00:28:20.140 align:middle line:10%
and using their group
energy, so to speak,

00:28:20.140 --> 00:28:22.130 align:middle line:10%
to try and contact the spirits.

00:28:22.130 --> 00:28:24.730 align:middle line:10%
It was another American
innovation that started getting

00:28:24.730 --> 00:28:28.420 align:middle line:10%
practiced in upstate New York,
and it was something that

00:28:28.420 --> 00:28:33.250 align:middle line:10%
Americans exported in the 1850s
when sances began to occur

00:28:33.250 --> 00:28:35.500 align:middle line:10%
in the salons of Paris and Rome.

00:28:35.500 --> 00:28:39.280 align:middle line:84%
But in its modern form, it
began right here in the US,

00:28:39.280 --> 00:28:40.702 align:middle line:90%
and it is still practiced today.

00:28:40.702 --> 00:28:42.160 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They
somehow had something

00:28:42.160 --> 00:28:43.750 align:middle line:84%
to do with the women's
rights movement?

00:28:43.750 --> 00:28:44.440 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Oh, yes, sir.

00:28:44.440 --> 00:28:45.240 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: How so?

00:28:45.240 --> 00:28:47.500 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: Back in the day,
most mediums were women,

00:28:47.500 --> 00:28:49.960 align:middle line:10%
and it provided the
first opening in America.

00:28:49.960 --> 00:28:53.350 align:middle line:10%
This goes back to the
1840s, 1850s, for women

00:28:53.350 --> 00:28:56.740 align:middle line:10%
to have a voice in the religious
and civic life of the country.

00:28:56.740 --> 00:28:58.820 align:middle line:84%
Sances were a big
deal back in the day.

00:28:58.820 --> 00:29:01.030 align:middle line:84%
People formed into
sance societies.

00:29:01.030 --> 00:29:03.430 align:middle line:10%
They had their own newspapers,
their own newsletters,

00:29:03.430 --> 00:29:06.860 align:middle line:10%
and women who wanted to be
heard could be heard as leaders,

00:29:06.860 --> 00:29:08.780 align:middle line:10%
as mediums, at the sance table.

00:29:08.780 --> 00:29:11.480 align:middle line:10%
And this coincided with the dawn
of the women's rights movement.

00:29:11.480 --> 00:29:14.110 align:middle line:84%
The two movements really
intersected for many years.

00:29:14.110 --> 00:29:16.540 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: The Lincoln White
House was big into sances.

00:29:16.540 --> 00:29:17.200 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Oh, for real.

00:29:17.200 --> 00:29:17.470 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Were they not?

00:29:17.470 --> 00:29:18.345 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: For real.

00:29:18.345 --> 00:29:20.140 align:middle line:10%
I read about this
in "Occult America."

00:29:20.140 --> 00:29:23.800 align:middle line:10%
Abe and Mary Todd Lincoln
conducted at least two sances

00:29:23.800 --> 00:29:25.480 align:middle line:10%
that we know about
in the White House.

00:29:25.480 --> 00:29:27.430 align:middle line:10%
They permitted a reporter
from the newspaper,

00:29:27.430 --> 00:29:30.750 align:middle line:10%
the "Boston Gazette" to
be present at one of them.

00:29:30.750 --> 00:29:33.288 align:middle line:10%
And they did these in the
Red Room of the White House.

00:29:33.288 --> 00:29:34.580 align:middle line:10%
And it's absolutely remarkable.

00:29:34.580 --> 00:29:38.150 align:middle line:84%
Abe Lincoln was participating
in this occult ceremony

00:29:38.150 --> 00:29:40.282 align:middle line:84%
that a lot of Americans
were at the time.

00:29:40.282 --> 00:29:42.740 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Didn't he have his
own dream of his assassination?

00:29:42.740 --> 00:29:43.740 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Yes, he did.

00:29:43.740 --> 00:29:45.410 align:middle line:10%
Lincoln had a lot
of prophetic dreams,

00:29:45.410 --> 00:29:48.080 align:middle line:10%
and he had a dream of his
assassination, one of which

00:29:48.080 --> 00:29:50.930 align:middle line:10%
involved seeing two images
of himself in a mirror,

00:29:50.930 --> 00:29:52.612 align:middle line:10%
and then one of
the images faded.

00:29:52.612 --> 00:29:55.070 align:middle line:10%
And Mary Todd interpreted that
as a dream of his own death.

00:29:55.070 --> 00:29:56.990 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Now she was big
into this, too, wasn't she?

00:29:56.990 --> 00:29:58.573 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: Until
the end of her life.

00:29:58.573 --> 00:29:59.760 align:middle line:90%
Until the end of her life.

00:29:59.760 --> 00:30:02.240 align:middle line:10%
In fact, Mary Todd worked
directly towards the end of her

00:30:02.240 --> 00:30:05.420 align:middle line:10%
life with one of the
young girls, Margaret Fox,

00:30:05.420 --> 00:30:08.370 align:middle line:10%
who had popularized spiritualism
and sances in upstate New

00:30:08.370 --> 00:30:09.170 align:middle line:10%
York.

00:30:09.170 --> 00:30:10.610 align:middle line:90%
Mary Todd was a believer.

00:30:10.610 --> 00:30:12.118 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: So was Nancy Reagan.

00:30:12.118 --> 00:30:13.160 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Oh, for real.

00:30:13.160 --> 00:30:13.820 align:middle line:90%
For real.

00:30:13.820 --> 00:30:14.180 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Huge.

00:30:14.180 --> 00:30:16.700 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: The Reagans
spent 30 years of their lives

00:30:16.700 --> 00:30:19.040 align:middle line:84%
in Southern California,
and they picked up

00:30:19.040 --> 00:30:22.370 align:middle line:84%
on the social mores and the
practices of the region.

00:30:22.370 --> 00:30:24.980 align:middle line:10%
They were pals with the
psychic Jeane Dixon.

00:30:24.980 --> 00:30:29.030 align:middle line:84%
But Jeane failed to predict
Ron's rise to the White House.

00:30:29.030 --> 00:30:31.430 align:middle line:10%
So Nancy broke with
Jeane and later became

00:30:31.430 --> 00:30:34.880 align:middle line:10%
pals with an astrologer
named Joan Quigley, who

00:30:34.880 --> 00:30:36.450 align:middle line:10%
lived in San Francisco.

00:30:36.450 --> 00:30:38.270 align:middle line:10%
And she was friends
with Joan at the time

00:30:38.270 --> 00:30:39.470 align:middle line:10%
when all this got exposed.

00:30:39.470 --> 00:30:41.090 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But Jeane
Dixon predicted

00:30:41.090 --> 00:30:42.650 align:middle line:90%
Kennedy's assassination.

00:30:42.650 --> 00:30:43.550 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: She did.

00:30:43.550 --> 00:30:47.150 align:middle line:10%
In 1956, speaking to
"Parade Magazine,"

00:30:47.150 --> 00:30:50.540 align:middle line:10%
Jeane Dixon said that the next
presidential election would

00:30:50.540 --> 00:30:55.610 align:middle line:10%
be won by a young brown
haired man, very robust,

00:30:55.610 --> 00:30:58.220 align:middle line:10%
would have the support of
Labor, the support of the Labor

00:30:58.220 --> 00:31:01.430 align:middle line:10%
Movement behind him, and would
die by an assassin's bullet

00:31:01.430 --> 00:31:03.890 align:middle line:10%
in his first year in office.

00:31:03.890 --> 00:31:04.820 align:middle line:90%
Pretty eerie.

00:31:04.820 --> 00:31:06.500 align:middle line:90%
Pretty spot on.

00:31:06.500 --> 00:31:08.300 align:middle line:84%
In fairness, I also
have to say, Jeane

00:31:08.300 --> 00:31:11.180 align:middle line:84%
made hundreds of predictions
that didn't come true.

00:31:11.180 --> 00:31:14.590 align:middle line:84%
But she did get a hit there, and
it made her famous, actually.

00:31:14.590 --> 00:31:15.840 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah, after the fact.

00:31:15.840 --> 00:31:16.050 align:middle line:90%
I remember--

00:31:16.050 --> 00:31:16.310 align:middle line:90%
After the fact.

00:31:16.310 --> 00:31:18.320 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: --"Life" magazine
writing about her.

00:31:18.320 --> 00:31:18.740 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: That's right.

00:31:18.740 --> 00:31:19.700 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Or "Look" magazine.

00:31:19.700 --> 00:31:20.742 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: That's right.

00:31:20.742 --> 00:31:22.550 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And she was
a pretty big story.

00:31:22.550 --> 00:31:24.110 align:middle line:84%
My mother used to
talk about her.

00:31:24.110 --> 00:31:25.527 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: Jeane
was a big story.

00:31:25.527 --> 00:31:27.230 align:middle line:10%
And believe it or
not, Jeane actually

00:31:27.230 --> 00:31:30.705 align:middle line:10%
had an Oval Office session
with Richard Nixon.

00:31:30.705 --> 00:31:31.505 align:middle line:90%
Not a president--

00:31:31.505 --> 00:31:31.850 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Really?

00:31:31.850 --> 00:31:33.592 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: --known
for occult passions,

00:31:33.592 --> 00:31:35.300 align:middle line:84%
but they sat in the
Oval Office together.

00:31:35.300 --> 00:31:37.800 align:middle line:84%
She gave him advice on
a variety of things.

00:31:37.800 --> 00:31:39.500 align:middle line:10%
And the reason we
know about it is

00:31:39.500 --> 00:31:41.780 align:middle line:10%
because it's preserved
on the Watergate tapes.

00:31:41.780 --> 00:31:44.700 align:middle line:10%
Nixon was recording almost
everything in the Oval Office

00:31:44.700 --> 00:31:45.500 align:middle line:10%
at that time.

00:31:45.500 --> 00:31:47.625 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, again, she
was the one who predicted

00:31:47.625 --> 00:31:49.070 align:middle line:90%
Kennedy's victory over Nixon.

00:31:49.070 --> 00:31:50.070 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: That's true.

00:31:50.070 --> 00:31:50.970 align:middle line:90%
That's true.

00:31:50.970 --> 00:31:55.100 align:middle line:10%
And Nixon's secretary was a
big fan of Dixon's, and she

00:31:55.100 --> 00:31:58.250 align:middle line:10%
convinced him to have a session
with him, and he agreed.

00:31:58.250 --> 00:32:00.470 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You're considered
an occult expert.

00:32:00.470 --> 00:32:03.560 align:middle line:84%
Does that mean you dabble
with the dark side?

00:32:03.560 --> 00:32:04.710 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: I do, George.

00:32:04.710 --> 00:32:06.460 align:middle line:90%
I am a believing historian.

00:32:06.460 --> 00:32:07.260 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Ee.

00:32:07.260 --> 00:32:08.690 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Well, I'm sorry.

00:32:08.690 --> 00:32:10.490 align:middle line:90%
I'm a nice guy, too, I think.

00:32:10.490 --> 00:32:13.280 align:middle line:10%
And I believe in
many of the things

00:32:13.280 --> 00:32:15.620 align:middle line:10%
that I write about as an
experiment or as a seeker,

00:32:15.620 --> 00:32:16.420 align:middle line:10%
as an explorer.

00:32:16.420 --> 00:32:19.040 align:middle line:10%
Of course, my conception
of what the dark side is,

00:32:19.040 --> 00:32:21.320 align:middle line:10%
is different from
what people commonly

00:32:21.320 --> 00:32:22.760 align:middle line:10%
mean when they use that term.

00:32:22.760 --> 00:32:26.000 align:middle line:10%
I have a code, a sense of
ethics, a sense of honor,

00:32:26.000 --> 00:32:27.470 align:middle line:10%
a sense of loyalty.

00:32:27.470 --> 00:32:30.350 align:middle line:10%
My wish is to do nothing that
would hurt, or humiliate,

00:32:30.350 --> 00:32:33.962 align:middle line:10%
or harm anybody, but I am
very much an experimenter

00:32:33.962 --> 00:32:35.420 align:middle line:10%
into the realms
that I write about.

00:32:35.420 --> 00:32:37.530 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: But why do you
dabble with the dark side?

00:32:37.530 --> 00:32:39.230 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: Well, George,
I really believe--

00:32:39.230 --> 00:32:41.270 align:middle line:10%
I have to be frank with
you and your listeners.

00:32:41.270 --> 00:32:43.940 align:middle line:10%
For a long time, I was
on the spiritual search,

00:32:43.940 --> 00:32:46.440 align:middle line:10%
and I was asking myself,
what am I looking for?

00:32:46.440 --> 00:32:47.760 align:middle line:10%
What am I looking for?

00:32:47.760 --> 00:32:50.090 align:middle line:10%
And the simple
uncensored truth is

00:32:50.090 --> 00:32:52.220 align:middle line:10%
that I came to feel
after a certain point

00:32:52.220 --> 00:32:54.020 align:middle line:10%
that what I was
really looking for

00:32:54.020 --> 00:32:56.720 align:middle line:10%
was personal power in the way
that someone like Nietzsche

00:32:56.720 --> 00:32:58.490 align:middle line:10%
was looking for, for example.

00:32:58.490 --> 00:33:00.743 align:middle line:84%
And I came to that through
my sense of the occult

00:33:00.743 --> 00:33:02.160 align:middle line:84%
and through esoteric
spirituality.

00:33:02.160 --> 00:33:03.200 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And have
you found that?

00:33:03.200 --> 00:33:04.370 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: I think I have.

00:33:04.370 --> 00:33:05.930 align:middle line:10%
I've never been
happier in my life.

00:33:05.930 --> 00:33:07.340 align:middle line:10%
I'm 53 years old today.

00:33:07.340 --> 00:33:10.700 align:middle line:10%
I'm doing everything that
I wish to do in life.

00:33:10.700 --> 00:33:11.750 align:middle line:10%
I've never been happier.

00:33:11.750 --> 00:33:14.070 align:middle line:10%
I've never been surrounded
by a greater group of people

00:33:14.070 --> 00:33:14.870 align:middle line:10%
that I love.

00:33:14.870 --> 00:33:16.725 align:middle line:10%
I've never had better
working relationships.

00:33:16.725 --> 00:33:19.100 align:middle line:10%
I feel I've come to things
that have been very personally

00:33:19.100 --> 00:33:22.042 align:middle line:10%
important to me, which I wish
for you and everybody watching.

00:33:22.042 --> 00:33:23.750 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, you're
not an evil person.

00:33:23.750 --> 00:33:24.830 align:middle line:90%
I've known you for years.

00:33:24.830 --> 00:33:25.130 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Thank you.

00:33:25.130 --> 00:33:27.210 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I don't consider
you to be a bad person.

00:33:27.210 --> 00:33:28.627 align:middle line:84%
Have you ever been
scared, though,

00:33:28.627 --> 00:33:30.170 align:middle line:90%
dabbling with the dark side?

00:33:30.170 --> 00:33:32.600 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: In all honesty,
George, I have not.

00:33:32.600 --> 00:33:35.150 align:middle line:10%
I have not once been scared
dabbling with the dark side

00:33:35.150 --> 00:33:36.210 align:middle line:10%
in my entire life.

00:33:36.210 --> 00:33:39.050 align:middle line:10%
And I've tried some
pretty far out things.

00:33:39.050 --> 00:33:41.060 align:middle line:10%
The search is very
important to me.

00:33:41.060 --> 00:33:42.980 align:middle line:10%
And again, although
I have a strong code

00:33:42.980 --> 00:33:45.000 align:middle line:10%
of honor, a strong
code of ethics,

00:33:45.000 --> 00:33:47.150 align:middle line:10%
there's almost
nothing I won't try.

00:33:47.150 --> 00:33:48.650 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Have you
tried tarot cards?

00:33:48.650 --> 00:33:50.817 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: Oh, sure, I
work with them all the time.

00:33:50.817 --> 00:33:54.320 align:middle line:84%
I do readings for
myself, for other people.

00:33:54.320 --> 00:33:57.020 align:middle line:84%
I believe there is a
real strong foresightful

00:33:57.020 --> 00:33:59.760 align:middle line:84%
quality to tarot cards, and
I use them quite frequently,

00:33:59.760 --> 00:34:00.560 align:middle line:90%
actually.

00:34:00.560 --> 00:34:03.210 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What is it about
the cards that seems to work?

00:34:03.210 --> 00:34:04.500 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: You know, it's
an interesting question.

00:34:04.500 --> 00:34:06.080 align:middle line:10%
I've pondered that
frequently myself,

00:34:06.080 --> 00:34:08.850 align:middle line:10%
and I think it goes back to what
we were talking about earlier.

00:34:08.850 --> 00:34:12.350 align:middle line:10%
It's possible that every
frozen moment in time

00:34:12.350 --> 00:34:15.630 align:middle line:10%
demonstrates or symbolizes
everything that's going on.

00:34:15.630 --> 00:34:18.980 align:middle line:10%
So if you can use a
pictogrammatic device,

00:34:18.980 --> 00:34:22.790 align:middle line:10%
like tarot, or like the I Ching,
or something along those lines,

00:34:22.790 --> 00:34:25.159 align:middle line:10%
you can gain kind of a
multi-dimensional snapshot

00:34:25.159 --> 00:34:27.590 align:middle line:10%
of everything that's
happening in a certain moment.

00:34:27.590 --> 00:34:30.400 align:middle line:10%
And in my experience,
they do seem to work.

00:34:30.400 --> 00:34:32.980 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What generates the
accuracy of the tarot cards,

00:34:32.980 --> 00:34:36.400 align:middle line:84%
the individual who reads
them or the individual

00:34:36.400 --> 00:34:37.613 align:middle line:90%
who is being read about?

00:34:37.613 --> 00:34:39.280 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: That's a
wonderful question.

00:34:39.280 --> 00:34:41.253 align:middle line:10%
In my personal
experience, I think

00:34:41.253 --> 00:34:42.670 align:middle line:10%
it's the individual
who reads them

00:34:42.670 --> 00:34:45.320 align:middle line:10%
because I will do distance
tarot readings for people,

00:34:45.320 --> 00:34:46.120 align:middle line:10%
for example.

00:34:46.120 --> 00:34:46.989 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: You pull the card?

00:34:46.989 --> 00:34:48.880 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: Oh, yeah,
I'll pull cards for--

00:34:48.880 --> 00:34:51.250 align:middle line:10%
I'll do a simple
three card spread.

00:34:51.250 --> 00:34:53.590 align:middle line:10%
And I'll pull cards for people
and communicate with them

00:34:53.590 --> 00:34:54.699 align:middle line:10%
over email.

00:34:54.699 --> 00:34:57.010 align:middle line:10%
Time, distance, the
person asking-- it

00:34:57.010 --> 00:34:58.300 align:middle line:10%
doesn't seem to matter.

00:34:58.300 --> 00:35:00.700 align:middle line:10%
Most of the people who get
these readings come back to me

00:35:00.700 --> 00:35:03.172 align:middle line:10%
and say, I did experience
something poignant.

00:35:03.172 --> 00:35:04.880 align:middle line:10%
I feel you put your
fingers on something.

00:35:04.880 --> 00:35:06.160 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you pull
one card or three?

00:35:06.160 --> 00:35:07.702 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: I pull
three cards, and I

00:35:07.702 --> 00:35:09.130 align:middle line:84%
look for a storyline
in the cards,

00:35:09.130 --> 00:35:11.140 align:middle line:84%
almost as if I was
reading a comic strip.

00:35:11.140 --> 00:35:13.450 align:middle line:84%
I might read it right
to left, left to right.

00:35:13.450 --> 00:35:16.060 align:middle line:84%
I might have the two cards
impact on the center card.

00:35:16.060 --> 00:35:18.855 align:middle line:84%
But I'm looking for a
story within the images.

00:35:18.855 --> 00:35:20.480 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What does
the death card mean?

00:35:20.480 --> 00:35:22.550 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: Mm, good question.

00:35:22.550 --> 00:35:24.493 align:middle line:10%
Most of these things
are metaphorical.

00:35:24.493 --> 00:35:26.410 align:middle line:10%
If I were to pull the
death card for somebody,

00:35:26.410 --> 00:35:29.440 align:middle line:10%
I wouldn't say that
physical demise is eminent.

00:35:29.440 --> 00:35:31.930 align:middle line:10%
Most of the time, it does
signify the end of something.

00:35:31.930 --> 00:35:34.475 align:middle line:10%
And look, George, I've pulled
the death card for myself.

00:35:34.475 --> 00:35:36.100 align:middle line:10%
There have been
relationships that I've

00:35:36.100 --> 00:35:38.235 align:middle line:10%
been in that I very
much wanted to work,

00:35:38.235 --> 00:35:40.360 align:middle line:10%
and I've pulled the death
card and I've said, look,

00:35:40.360 --> 00:35:41.895 align:middle line:10%
you can make
excuses, but you have

00:35:41.895 --> 00:35:44.020 align:middle line:10%
to come to terms with what
you're being shown here.

00:35:44.020 --> 00:35:45.813 align:middle line:10%
And those relationships did end.

00:35:45.813 --> 00:35:47.480 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Or a job or
anything like that.

00:35:47.480 --> 00:35:47.610 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Oh, sure.

00:35:47.610 --> 00:35:49.900 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It doesn't necessarily
mean your life is over.

00:35:49.900 --> 00:35:51.983 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: No, it doesn't
mean your life is over.

00:35:51.983 --> 00:35:54.850 align:middle line:10%
And look, you know, I think
that there have been things

00:35:54.850 --> 00:35:57.225 align:middle line:10%
that I've wanted in life
that I have not gotten,

00:35:57.225 --> 00:35:59.350 align:middle line:10%
and I have been very grateful
I haven't gotten them

00:35:59.350 --> 00:36:01.517 align:middle line:10%
because they've opened the
door to something better.

00:36:01.517 --> 00:36:04.600 align:middle line:10%
And the thing I was pursuing may
have been ruinous in some way.

00:36:04.600 --> 00:36:07.205 align:middle line:10%
So no can be the best thing
that ever happens to us.

00:36:07.205 --> 00:36:09.400 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are you the
modern day Alister Crowley?

00:36:09.400 --> 00:36:11.530 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: Oh, that's a
very interesting question.

00:36:11.530 --> 00:36:12.940 align:middle line:10%
I'd be very
flattered if somebody

00:36:12.940 --> 00:36:14.950 align:middle line:10%
called me the modern
day Alister Crowley,

00:36:14.950 --> 00:36:16.210 align:middle line:10%
although I would have to say--

00:36:16.210 --> 00:36:17.043 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: I just did.

00:36:17.043 --> 00:36:18.490 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: Ah, you just did.

00:36:18.490 --> 00:36:21.190 align:middle line:10%
I believe, personally
speaking, I

00:36:21.190 --> 00:36:24.400 align:middle line:10%
strive to have a stronger
sense of personal ethics

00:36:24.400 --> 00:36:27.250 align:middle line:10%
and a stronger code of honor
than I believe Crowley did.

00:36:27.250 --> 00:36:30.258 align:middle line:10%
Crowley was a great man,
but I would not personally

00:36:30.258 --> 00:36:32.800 align:middle line:10%
have been one of his students
because I think a lot of people

00:36:32.800 --> 00:36:34.240 align:middle line:10%
got hurt around him.

00:36:34.240 --> 00:36:37.270 align:middle line:84%
And I don't think he
demonstrated sufficient loyalty

00:36:37.270 --> 00:36:39.670 align:middle line:84%
or sufficient compassion
towards other people.

00:36:39.670 --> 00:36:41.560 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: People
thought he was evil.

00:36:41.560 --> 00:36:43.120 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: He
cultivated that image.

00:36:43.120 --> 00:36:44.680 align:middle line:84%
He wanted to be
thought of as evil.

00:36:44.680 --> 00:36:45.190 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Really?

00:36:45.190 --> 00:36:45.910 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: Oh,
he was the one who

00:36:45.910 --> 00:36:47.380 align:middle line:10%
called himself the great beast.

00:36:47.380 --> 00:36:50.260 align:middle line:10%
And he loved when the English
tabloids would mix it up

00:36:50.260 --> 00:36:51.980 align:middle line:10%
and call him names and so on.

00:36:51.980 --> 00:36:53.130 align:middle line:10%
He was a great artist.

00:36:53.130 --> 00:36:54.370 align:middle line:10%
He was a great pioneer.

00:36:54.370 --> 00:36:56.410 align:middle line:10%
And he was a great intellect.

00:36:56.410 --> 00:37:00.070 align:middle line:10%
But he didn't have a
sufficiently developed sense

00:37:00.070 --> 00:37:01.370 align:middle line:10%
of personal ethics.

00:37:01.370 --> 00:37:03.640 align:middle line:10%
And I think that was his
downfall as a teacher.

00:37:03.640 --> 00:37:05.440 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Your latest book is
called "The Miracle Club."

00:37:05.440 --> 00:37:05.860 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Yes, sir.

00:37:05.860 --> 00:37:07.090 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What is
the miracle club?

00:37:07.090 --> 00:37:09.507 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: The miracle club
was a group of occult seekers

00:37:09.507 --> 00:37:12.010 align:middle line:10%
who gathered in New
York City in 1875,

00:37:12.010 --> 00:37:14.620 align:middle line:10%
and their wish was to
explore the beyond.

00:37:14.620 --> 00:37:17.200 align:middle line:10%
And they included people
like Madame HP Blavatsky,

00:37:17.200 --> 00:37:19.510 align:middle line:10%
the great co-founder
of theosophy.

00:37:19.510 --> 00:37:21.670 align:middle line:10%
And they only stayed
together a few months,

00:37:21.670 --> 00:37:23.500 align:middle line:10%
but they were very influential.

00:37:23.500 --> 00:37:26.440 align:middle line:10%
They formed the larger
theosophical organization

00:37:26.440 --> 00:37:27.970 align:middle line:10%
that's so popular today.

00:37:27.970 --> 00:37:29.780 align:middle line:10%
And their slogan was one word--

00:37:29.780 --> 00:37:30.580 align:middle line:10%
try.

00:37:30.580 --> 00:37:31.570 align:middle line:10%
Try.

00:37:31.570 --> 00:37:33.160 align:middle line:10%
And I was very
inspired by that so I

00:37:33.160 --> 00:37:36.580 align:middle line:10%
named the new book an homage
to the original miracle club.

00:37:36.580 --> 00:37:39.018 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: The laws of success,
tell us about Napoleon Hill.

00:37:39.018 --> 00:37:41.560 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: Napoleon Hill has
been a great inspiration on me.

00:37:41.560 --> 00:37:43.390 align:middle line:10%
He wrote the book,
"Think and Grow Rich."

00:37:43.390 --> 00:37:44.300 align:middle line:90%
And his writing is very--

00:37:44.300 --> 00:37:45.100 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That was his big book.

00:37:45.100 --> 00:37:46.517 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: That
was his big book.

00:37:46.517 --> 00:37:48.050 align:middle line:90%
His writing is very simple.

00:37:48.050 --> 00:37:49.250 align:middle line:90%
It's very accessible.

00:37:49.250 --> 00:37:52.360 align:middle line:10%
But his ideas were much
richer and much deeper

00:37:52.360 --> 00:37:54.070 align:middle line:10%
than I think most
people have understood.

00:37:54.070 --> 00:37:57.340 align:middle line:10%
And I tell you, George, I
reread "Think and Grow Rich"

00:37:57.340 --> 00:37:58.870 align:middle line:10%
once every year.

00:37:58.870 --> 00:37:59.770 align:middle line:10%
I love the man.

00:37:59.770 --> 00:38:00.620 align:middle line:90%
I love the book.

00:38:00.620 --> 00:38:02.055 align:middle line:84%
It's been a huge
help in my life.

00:38:02.055 --> 00:38:03.930 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Let's look at
a vintage clip of him.

00:38:03.930 --> 00:38:05.124 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: All right.

00:38:05.124 --> 00:38:05.940 align:middle line:90%
