00:38:05.940 --> 00:38:08.890 align:middle line:84%
>> And now may I request that
you forget all your problems

00:38:08.890 --> 00:38:12.520 align:middle line:84%
and just relax while I bring you
the master key with which you

00:38:12.520 --> 00:38:15.550 align:middle line:84%
may unlock the door for any
opportunities that your mind

00:38:15.550 --> 00:38:17.440 align:middle line:90%
can conceive.

00:38:17.440 --> 00:38:22.270 align:middle line:84%
The master key consists of 17
principles, the first of which

00:38:22.270 --> 00:38:25.680 align:middle line:90%
is definiteness of purpose.

00:38:25.680 --> 00:38:28.660 align:middle line:84%
Right here at the
beginning of our visit,

00:38:28.660 --> 00:38:31.660 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to make you a promise.

00:38:31.660 --> 00:38:34.750 align:middle line:84%
If you will decide
definitely what you want most

00:38:34.750 --> 00:38:37.570 align:middle line:84%
during your entire
lifetime and write it down

00:38:37.570 --> 00:38:40.870 align:middle line:84%
on paper so that
I can read it, I

00:38:40.870 --> 00:38:42.730 align:middle line:84%
will give you the master
key with which you

00:38:42.730 --> 00:38:46.160 align:middle line:84%
may open the door to the
attainment of your desires,

00:38:46.160 --> 00:38:48.880 align:middle line:90%
whatever they may be.

00:38:48.880 --> 00:38:52.270 align:middle line:84%
The exact moment when I will
deliver this master key to you

00:38:52.270 --> 00:38:57.280 align:middle line:84%
will depend entirely upon when
you are ready to receive it.

00:38:57.280 --> 00:39:01.550 align:middle line:84%
This is the first of 13 messages
that I will deliver to you.

00:39:01.550 --> 00:39:04.560 align:middle line:84%
Now in each message, I will
describe the magic key in terms

00:39:04.560 --> 00:39:08.495 align:middle line:84%
that you will understand, if
you are ready to understand.

00:39:08.495 --> 00:39:09.295 align:middle line:90%
[END PLAYBACK]

00:39:09.295 --> 00:39:11.440 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Now that, of course,
was Harry Truman playing

00:39:11.440 --> 00:39:12.520 align:middle line:90%
the part of Napoleon Hill.

00:39:12.520 --> 00:39:13.280 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Well put.

00:39:13.280 --> 00:39:14.680 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: He looked
just like him.

00:39:14.680 --> 00:39:16.222 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: Yes,
they did look alike.

00:39:16.222 --> 00:39:19.550 align:middle line:10%
And I love the clip that you
selected because Hill really

00:39:19.550 --> 00:39:20.350 align:middle line:10%
lays it out.

00:39:20.350 --> 00:39:23.470 align:middle line:10%
He said the first point,
the key to everything

00:39:23.470 --> 00:39:25.420 align:middle line:10%
is to have a definite chief aim.

00:39:25.420 --> 00:39:27.010 align:middle line:10%
It's so vital.

00:39:27.010 --> 00:39:29.652 align:middle line:10%
And I could tell you and your
viewers what the master key is.

00:39:29.652 --> 00:39:30.860 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: I'd love to hear it.

00:39:30.860 --> 00:39:32.485 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: Please,
I'll lay it on you.

00:39:32.485 --> 00:39:33.720 align:middle line:10%
Thoughts are causative.

00:39:33.720 --> 00:39:34.820 align:middle line:10%
Thoughts are causative.

00:39:34.820 --> 00:39:35.710 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: What does that mean?

00:39:35.710 --> 00:39:37.918 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: It means that
your thoughts will actually

00:39:37.918 --> 00:39:41.730 align:middle line:10%
make things happen, but only
if you are absolutely focused.

00:39:41.730 --> 00:39:44.820 align:middle line:10%
You have to have one
passionate desire that you

00:39:44.820 --> 00:39:46.315 align:middle line:10%
want like breath itself.

00:39:46.315 --> 00:39:47.940 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It's
manifestation once again.

00:39:47.940 --> 00:39:48.740 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Yes.

00:39:48.740 --> 00:39:50.760 align:middle line:10%
But most of us go
through life having

00:39:50.760 --> 00:39:53.010 align:middle line:10%
a whole mishmash of
competing desires,

00:39:53.010 --> 00:39:56.552 align:middle line:10%
or we're afraid to choose one
desire, or we tell ourselves,

00:39:56.552 --> 00:39:58.260 align:middle line:10%
we know what our desire
is without really

00:39:58.260 --> 00:39:59.550 align:middle line:10%
being frank about it.

00:39:59.550 --> 00:40:02.400 align:middle line:10%
And Hill's genius was
he realized all this.

00:40:02.400 --> 00:40:04.710 align:middle line:10%
He realized this problem
in human nature, which

00:40:04.710 --> 00:40:07.980 align:middle line:10%
is that we think we know what
we want without really asking

00:40:07.980 --> 00:40:11.190 align:middle line:10%
ourselves that question in
a mature, and unembarrassed,

00:40:11.190 --> 00:40:12.215 align:middle line:10%
and intimate way.

00:40:12.215 --> 00:40:14.340 align:middle line:10%
If you could do that-- and
you have to tell anybody

00:40:14.340 --> 00:40:15.810 align:middle line:10%
the answer, it's private--

00:40:15.810 --> 00:40:18.180 align:middle line:10%
but if you can
arrive at that aim,

00:40:18.180 --> 00:40:20.550 align:middle line:10%
things start happening in
your life, and all the tools

00:40:20.550 --> 00:40:22.813 align:middle line:10%
that Hill talks about
become available to you.

00:40:22.813 --> 00:40:23.730 align:middle line:90%
That's the master key.

00:40:23.730 --> 00:40:25.830 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What about
this manifestation?

00:40:25.830 --> 00:40:27.240 align:middle line:90%
What about negativity?

00:40:27.240 --> 00:40:29.910 align:middle line:84%
What if negativity pops
up, crops up in this?

00:40:29.910 --> 00:40:31.358 align:middle line:90%
Does that kind of temper it?

00:40:31.358 --> 00:40:33.150 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: It can
temper it, but the truth

00:40:33.150 --> 00:40:35.340 align:middle line:10%
is if you really know
what you want in life,

00:40:35.340 --> 00:40:38.250 align:middle line:10%
not only does it serve to
amp up your enthusiasm,

00:40:38.250 --> 00:40:41.130 align:middle line:10%
but it will keep
negativity at bay.

00:40:41.130 --> 00:40:42.930 align:middle line:10%
I'm wracked with
negative thoughts.

00:40:42.930 --> 00:40:44.730 align:middle line:10%
I've never struggled
with depression,

00:40:44.730 --> 00:40:47.720 align:middle line:10%
but I have struggled
with anxiety all my life.

00:40:47.720 --> 00:40:50.490 align:middle line:10%
And I've found that when I came
in touch with what I really

00:40:50.490 --> 00:40:54.000 align:middle line:10%
wanted to be doing in
life, that anxiety receded.

00:40:54.000 --> 00:40:56.190 align:middle line:10%
It didn't vanish,
but it receded.

00:40:56.190 --> 00:40:59.490 align:middle line:10%
Having that one
obsessive passionate aim

00:40:59.490 --> 00:41:01.230 align:middle line:10%
can do so much
for an individual.

00:41:01.230 --> 00:41:02.850 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You have
written that there

00:41:02.850 --> 00:41:05.430 align:middle line:84%
is one vital step that's
important to using

00:41:05.430 --> 00:41:06.540 align:middle line:90%
these powers of the mind.

00:41:06.540 --> 00:41:07.110 align:middle line:90%
What is that?

00:41:07.110 --> 00:41:08.068 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: It's focus.

00:41:08.068 --> 00:41:08.970 align:middle line:10%
It's absolute focus.

00:41:08.970 --> 00:41:10.480 align:middle line:10%
It's the law of nature.

00:41:10.480 --> 00:41:13.230 align:middle line:10%
If you look at nature,
focus is the central law

00:41:13.230 --> 00:41:15.210 align:middle line:10%
that creates force.

00:41:15.210 --> 00:41:18.360 align:middle line:10%
Photons of light
focused become a laser.

00:41:18.360 --> 00:41:19.740 align:middle line:10%
And most of us don't focus.

00:41:19.740 --> 00:41:23.370 align:middle line:10%
We have a wide dispersed
range of competing aims.

00:41:23.370 --> 00:41:25.930 align:middle line:10%
Some of them are in direct
contradiction to one another.

00:41:25.930 --> 00:41:28.950 align:middle line:10%
But if you can get down
to the one thing you want,

00:41:28.950 --> 00:41:30.600 align:middle line:10%
it can be
extraordinarily powerful.

00:41:30.600 --> 00:41:31.830 align:middle line:10%
We fear doing that.

00:41:31.830 --> 00:41:34.860 align:middle line:10%
We fear it because look, life
does make multiple demands

00:41:34.860 --> 00:41:35.660 align:middle line:10%
on us.

00:41:35.660 --> 00:41:36.420 align:middle line:10%
We're parents.

00:41:36.420 --> 00:41:37.050 align:middle line:10%
We're workers.

00:41:37.050 --> 00:41:37.950 align:middle line:10%
We're homemakers.

00:41:37.950 --> 00:41:39.820 align:middle line:10%
We're interested in our careers.

00:41:39.820 --> 00:41:43.360 align:middle line:10%
And I understand we all
have to fill those shoes.

00:41:43.360 --> 00:41:46.080 align:middle line:84%
But the tough, if
transcendent, bargain

00:41:46.080 --> 00:41:49.590 align:middle line:84%
that life strikes with us is
if you can choose one aim,

00:41:49.590 --> 00:41:51.770 align:middle line:84%
it will open up
extraordinary doors to you.

00:41:51.770 --> 00:41:54.930 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: ESP, Extra
Sensory Perception,

00:41:54.930 --> 00:41:56.100 align:middle line:90%
what does that tell you?

00:41:56.100 --> 00:41:57.930 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: ESP has
been demonstrated

00:41:57.930 --> 00:41:59.140 align:middle line:90%
in laboratory settings.

00:41:59.140 --> 00:42:00.790 align:middle line:90%
There's no question about that.

00:42:00.790 --> 00:42:03.390 align:middle line:10%
The work of my
hero, JB Rhine, who

00:42:03.390 --> 00:42:07.530 align:middle line:10%
pioneered scholarly ESP studies
at Duke University, that

00:42:07.530 --> 00:42:08.580 align:middle line:10%
alone tells us that.

00:42:08.580 --> 00:42:12.570 align:middle line:10%
JB was able to demonstrate
that certain individuals were

00:42:12.570 --> 00:42:16.500 align:middle line:10%
able to pass information back
and forth under strenuously

00:42:16.500 --> 00:42:19.380 align:middle line:10%
controlled conditions
somewhere in a way that

00:42:19.380 --> 00:42:20.880 align:middle line:10%
went beyond the five senses.

00:42:20.880 --> 00:42:24.360 align:middle line:84%
And JB, for decades and
decades, assembled this data.

00:42:24.360 --> 00:42:25.680 align:middle line:90%
No one's overturned it.

00:42:25.680 --> 00:42:27.450 align:middle line:90%
No one's disproved it.

00:42:27.450 --> 00:42:29.850 align:middle line:10%
People won't wrestle with
the implications of it

00:42:29.850 --> 00:42:33.810 align:middle line:10%
because the implications of JB's
data and the data of Dean Radin

00:42:33.810 --> 00:42:36.000 align:middle line:10%
and other people in
this field are that we

00:42:36.000 --> 00:42:37.890 align:middle line:10%
have a non-physical existence.

00:42:37.890 --> 00:42:40.620 align:middle line:10%
We are not just flesh and bone.

00:42:40.620 --> 00:42:43.620 align:middle line:10%
Information can pass
between us and other people

00:42:43.620 --> 00:42:45.062 align:middle line:10%
in an extra sensory manner.

00:42:45.062 --> 00:42:47.520 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did you ever look at
the work of my late aunt, Dr.

00:42:47.520 --> 00:42:48.942 align:middle line:90%
Shafica Karagulla?

00:42:48.942 --> 00:42:51.150 align:middle line:84%
She wrote a book called
"Breakthrough to Creativity."

00:42:51.150 --> 00:42:53.070 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: I know the name,
but I have not looked at it.

00:42:53.070 --> 00:42:54.480 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: She was a dear
friend of Ingo Swann,

00:42:54.480 --> 00:42:55.360 align:middle line:90%
the remote viewer.

00:42:55.360 --> 00:42:56.160 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Sure.

00:42:56.160 --> 00:42:57.810 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And she
was a psychiatrist.

00:42:57.810 --> 00:43:00.330 align:middle line:84%
Got her degree from
Oxford University

00:43:00.330 --> 00:43:06.450 align:middle line:84%
and decided to change her
entire practice from psychiatry

00:43:06.450 --> 00:43:08.307 align:middle line:90%
to studying telepathy and ESP.

00:43:08.307 --> 00:43:09.390 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: How wonderful.

00:43:09.390 --> 00:43:10.973 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: That's what
she wanted to do.

00:43:10.973 --> 00:43:12.880 align:middle line:84%
She ended up dying
in Beverly Hills

00:43:12.880 --> 00:43:16.390 align:middle line:84%
when a radio fell into her
tub, and she was taking a bath.

00:43:16.390 --> 00:43:17.190 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Wow.

00:43:17.190 --> 00:43:18.607 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And I'm
saying to myself,

00:43:18.607 --> 00:43:20.930 align:middle line:84%
I hope to God she wasn't
listening to my show

00:43:20.930 --> 00:43:21.840 align:middle line:90%
when that happened.

00:43:21.840 --> 00:43:24.390 align:middle line:84%
Thank god I wasn't
on the air then.

00:43:24.390 --> 00:43:29.310 align:middle line:84%
But she devoted her entire
practice to telepathy and ESP,

00:43:29.310 --> 00:43:31.890 align:middle line:84%
and she wrote incredible
books and research

00:43:31.890 --> 00:43:34.312 align:middle line:84%
that it really works
and it's powerful.

00:43:34.312 --> 00:43:35.520 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: I celebrate that.

00:43:35.520 --> 00:43:38.550 align:middle line:10%
I celebrate that because I
think when a lot of us go to see

00:43:38.550 --> 00:43:40.770 align:middle line:10%
shrinks, when a lot of
us go to see therapists--

00:43:40.770 --> 00:43:42.670 align:middle line:10%
and I go to one myself--

00:43:42.670 --> 00:43:44.790 align:middle line:10%
I think it's because we
feel a frustrated sense

00:43:44.790 --> 00:43:46.720 align:middle line:10%
of personal power in our lives.

00:43:46.720 --> 00:43:50.130 align:middle line:10%
But when somebody can expose
us to methods and ideas that

00:43:50.130 --> 00:43:52.470 align:middle line:10%
amp up our sense
of personal power,

00:43:52.470 --> 00:43:54.480 align:middle line:10%
our sense that we can
get done in the world

00:43:54.480 --> 00:43:57.240 align:middle line:10%
that which we seek to
do, these things that we

00:43:57.240 --> 00:44:00.460 align:middle line:10%
consider neuroses begin to
recede into the distance.

00:44:00.460 --> 00:44:03.900 align:middle line:10%
I think a lot of what we
consider to be neuroses,

00:44:03.900 --> 00:44:07.770 align:middle line:10%
or problems, or anxieties
reflect a frustrated sense

00:44:07.770 --> 00:44:08.940 align:middle line:10%
of personal power.

00:44:08.940 --> 00:44:11.340 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Have you
had cases of deja vu?

00:44:11.340 --> 00:44:13.170 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: I have
had many cases of what

00:44:13.170 --> 00:44:15.960 align:middle line:10%
I would call time collapses,
where past, present,

00:44:15.960 --> 00:44:18.300 align:middle line:10%
and future seem to be
playing out all at once.

00:44:18.300 --> 00:44:19.540 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Like you know
what's going to happen.

00:44:19.540 --> 00:44:19.835 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Absolutely.

00:44:19.835 --> 00:44:20.480 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Feeling.

00:44:20.480 --> 00:44:20.745 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Absolutely.

00:44:20.745 --> 00:44:21.780 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It's a weird feeling.

00:44:21.780 --> 00:44:23.363 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: It's a
very weird feeling,

00:44:23.363 --> 00:44:25.290 align:middle line:10%
and it gives you a
sense that time may not

00:44:25.290 --> 00:44:26.250 align:middle line:10%
be what we think it is.

00:44:26.250 --> 00:44:29.300 align:middle line:10%
We think of this very
orderly linear time,

00:44:29.300 --> 00:44:31.700 align:middle line:10%
but that just may be a
necessary device that we

00:44:31.700 --> 00:44:33.110 align:middle line:10%
use to get through the day.

00:44:33.110 --> 00:44:35.570 align:middle line:10%
It may be that everything
is going on at once, which

00:44:35.570 --> 00:44:37.550 align:middle line:10%
is what we understand
when we experience

00:44:37.550 --> 00:44:39.383 align:middle line:10%
deja vu, or synchronicity,
or time collapse.

00:44:39.383 --> 00:44:41.008 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Well, assuming
there's nothing

00:44:41.008 --> 00:44:42.270 align:middle line:10%
medically wrong with you.

00:44:42.270 --> 00:44:44.270 align:middle line:84%
You don't have some kind
of tumor in your brain.

00:44:44.270 --> 00:44:45.170 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Yes, sir.

00:44:45.170 --> 00:44:48.440 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I am convinced
that deja vu is

00:44:48.440 --> 00:44:51.740 align:middle line:84%
a crossing over of two
dimensions where there are

00:44:51.740 --> 00:44:54.620 align:middle line:84%
two Georges or two
Mitch Horowitzes,

00:44:54.620 --> 00:44:58.400 align:middle line:84%
and the one that's already
experienced that event somehow

00:44:58.400 --> 00:45:00.923 align:middle line:84%
crosses over, and
you pick it up.

00:45:00.923 --> 00:45:02.840 align:middle line:84%
>>HOROWITZ: Yes, I think
that's very well put.

00:45:02.840 --> 00:45:05.257 align:middle line:10%
And I think that's actually
backed up by things that we've

00:45:05.257 --> 00:45:09.050 align:middle line:10%
seen in 80 years of quantum
physics experiments, where

00:45:09.050 --> 00:45:12.710 align:middle line:10%
a particle can be in a so-called
state of superposition.

00:45:12.710 --> 00:45:14.840 align:middle line:84%
It can be everywhere
at once until somebody

00:45:14.840 --> 00:45:15.890 align:middle line:90%
takes a measurement.

00:45:15.890 --> 00:45:16.970 align:middle line:90%
Then it gets localized.

00:45:16.970 --> 00:45:19.010 align:middle line:90%
But it was in a wave state.

00:45:19.010 --> 00:45:21.230 align:middle line:84%
It was in this state
of superposition.

00:45:21.230 --> 00:45:23.060 align:middle line:84%
And that's akin to
what you're describing.

00:45:23.060 --> 00:45:24.120 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What are
your new works?

00:45:24.120 --> 00:45:25.412 align:middle line:90%
What are you working on, Mitch?

00:45:25.412 --> 00:45:28.010 align:middle line:10%
>>HOROWITZ: Well, I just
completed a 12-part video

00:45:28.010 --> 00:45:31.500 align:middle line:10%
series about the secret
teachings of all ages.

00:45:31.500 --> 00:45:34.730 align:middle line:10%
That's the great work
produced by Manly P. Hall.

00:45:34.730 --> 00:45:37.460 align:middle line:10%
That will go up at the
website of the University

00:45:37.460 --> 00:45:40.970 align:middle line:10%
of Philosophical
Research in June of 2019.

00:45:40.970 --> 00:45:42.800 align:middle line:10%
It's a 12-part
series that explores

00:45:42.800 --> 00:45:45.390 align:middle line:10%
all the occult and esoteric
themes in the book.

00:45:45.390 --> 00:45:48.180 align:middle line:10%
I just shot it in Los
Angeles last week.

00:45:48.180 --> 00:45:49.220 align:middle line:90%
I'm very proud of it.

00:45:49.220 --> 00:45:50.990 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And you travel
around the country still?

00:45:50.990 --> 00:45:51.990 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: Quite a bit.

00:45:51.990 --> 00:45:54.680 align:middle line:10%
I'll be speaking in
Pittsfield, Massachusetts.

00:45:54.680 --> 00:45:56.480 align:middle line:10%
I'll be speaking
in Virginia Beach.

00:45:56.480 --> 00:45:59.540 align:middle line:10%
I'll be speaking in Kansas
City, traveling all around.

00:45:59.540 --> 00:46:01.640 align:middle line:84%
And I love meeting
fellow seekers.

00:46:01.640 --> 00:46:03.687 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And people love
this topic, don't they?

00:46:03.687 --> 00:46:04.520 align:middle line:90%
>>HOROWITZ: They do.

00:46:04.520 --> 00:46:05.320 align:middle line:90%
They do.

00:46:05.320 --> 00:46:08.690 align:middle line:10%
They love feeling like in a
free-flowing, and intelligent,

00:46:08.690 --> 00:46:10.940 align:middle line:10%
and practical way,
they can talk about

00:46:10.940 --> 00:46:12.800 align:middle line:10%
